)@@G@@PE ANALYSIS PROCESSOR (RAT)   @]@@@@RIGHTM ON   @]@@@@HYPHEN ON   @]@@@@DL
)@@G@@1PURPOSE    @E@@@@ QUITE OFTEN A TAPE MAY MAGICALLY APPEAR FROM SOME UNKDM
)@@G@@NOWN  @E@@@@ SITE, CONSISTING OF SOME UNKNOWN QUANTITY OF UNKNOWN DATA. DN
)@@G@@@D@@@@ IT COULD BE ANY DENSITY OR PARITY. AND WHO KNOWS WHAT@E@@@@ CHARADO
)@@G@@CTER CODE IT WAS WRITTEN IN. THIS PROCESSOR HAS BEEN  @B@@@@ WRITTEN TO DP
)@@G@@HELP ALLEVIATE THE MYSTERY.   @]@@@@SPACE 1     @A@@@@ WHY RAT? BECAUSE DQ
)@@G@@IT 'READS A TAPE'.@#@@@@1PROCESSOR INPUT  @A@@@@ THE INPUT TO THE PROGRADR
)@@G@@M IS A TAPE.@]@@@@SPACE 1     @A@@@@ THE PROCESSOR IS CALLED BY ...     DS
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 1     @A@@@@     @RAT,<OPTIONS>   FILENAME.     @]@@@@SPACE DT
)@@G@@1     @E@@@@ THE ONLY OPTION CURRENTLY USED IS 'N'. THIS INDICATES THAT DU
)@@G@@@D@@@@ THE TAPE IS ALREADY IN THE CORRECT MODE FOR READING. @]@@@@SPACE DV
)@@G@@0     @F@@@@ THE FILENAME IS THE NAME OF THE PREVIOUSLY ASSIGNED TAPE FIDW
)@@G@@LE.   @]@@@@SPACE 1     @E@@@@ IT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE USER TO ADX
)@@G@@SSIGN THE TAPE    @D@@@@ TO A DRIVE THAT WILL BE ABLE TO READ IT. BUT INDY
)@@G@@ CASE @D@@@@ HE DOESN'T AND THE PROGRAM FAILS ALL ATTEMPTS, A     @D@@@@DZ
)@@G@@ SUGGESTION WILL BE MADE ABOUT TRYING A DIFFERENT TYPE@]@@@@ SERVO.     EA
)@@G@@@#@@@@1PROCESSOR OUTPUT @#@@@@2I/O ATTEMPTS     @E@@@@ THE RAT PROCESSOREB
)@@G@@ WILL TRY TO READ THE TAPE BY DYNAMICALLY @E@@@@ CHANGING THE PARITY ANDEC
)@@G@@ DENSITY MODES (IF THE 'N' OPTION   @E@@@@ IS NOT SPECIFIED) AND USING SED
)@@G@@UPPRESS RECOVERY MODE. FOR    @D@@@@ EVERY READ ATTEMPT, THE DENSITY ANDEE
)@@G@@ PARITY WILL BE   @#@@@@ PRINTED OUT.     @]@@@@SPACE 1     @E@@@@ ALL IEF
)@@G@@/O ATTEMPTS WILL BE DONE WITH TRANSLATIONS TURNED     @E@@@@ OFF. FOR MSEG
)@@G@@A DRIVES, THE MSA DATA TRANSFER FORMAT WILL     @D@@@@ BE THE SAME AS THEH
)@@G@@E ASSIGNMENT DEFAULTS, VIZ., FOR    @E@@@@ SEVEN TRACK DRIVES, 6-BIT PACEI
)@@G@@KED, FOR NINE TRACK DRIVES,   @#@@@@ 8-BIT PACKED.    @]@@@@SPACE 1     EJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@ A MAXUMUM OF 2048 WORDS CAN BE READ FROM THE TAPE. A WARNING     EK
)@@G@@@C@@@@ WILL BE ISSUED IF THE BLOCK COULD BE BIGGER.   @]@@@@2I/O STATUS EL
)@@G@@@E@@@@ FOR ALL READ ATTEMPTS THE I/O HARDWARE I/O STATUS' RETURNED@E@@@@EM
)@@G@@ BY THE EXEC WILL BE PRINTED. THIS WILL INCLUDE THE CONTENTS@E@@@@ OF LOEN
)@@G@@WER A1 FOR ALL READ ATTEMPTS AND THE MSA SENSE BYTES  @E@@@@ FOR U12/16/EO
)@@G@@20 SERVOS. IF ABNORMAL FRAME COUNT, END OF FILE,@E@@@@ OR END OF TAPE COEP
)@@G@@NDITIONS OCCUR, THE USER WILL BE INFORMED.@]@@@@SPACE 1     @E@@@@ IF A EQ
)@@G@@READ ATTEMPT FAILS AND DATA WAS PASSED ON THE TAPE,   @D@@@@ THE TAPE WIER
)@@G@@LL BE MOVED BACK A BLOCK BEFORE THE RETRY.@D@@@@ IF AN END OF FILE IS DEES
)@@G@@TECTED, THE NEXT BLOCK WILL BE@[@@@@ READ.@[@@@@2DUMPS@C@@@@ AS AN AID IET
)@@G@@N ANALYSING THE DATA ON THE TAPE,   @A@@@@ THE FIRST 64 WORDS OF THE BLOEU
)@@G@@CK    @E@@@@ WILL BE DUMPED IN VARIOUS FORMATS. CURRENTLY THESE INCLUDE EV
)@@G@@@E@@@@ OCTAL, HEXADECIMAL, FIELDATA, ASCII, EBCDIC, BCD AND XS-3. @E@@@@EW
)@@G@@ AFTER THE INITIAL DUMPS THE DATA WILL BE ASSUMED TO BE     @D@@@@ IN 8-EX
)@@G@@BIT PACKED FORMAT. (ALTHOUGH THIS IS USUALLY    @D@@@@ MEANINGFUL FOR NIEY
)@@G@@NE TRACK TAPES, ANY TAPE COULD BE   @D@@@@ IN THIS FORMAT. FOR EXAMPLE, EZ
)@@G@@ANSI LABELS.) THE DATA  @B@@@@ WILL BE 'UNPACKED' AND DUMPED AGAIN.     FA
)@@G@@@]@@@@SPACE 1     @E@@@@ IT IS ENTIRELY POSSIBLE THAT THE CHARACTER DUMPFB
)@@G@@S WOULD     @D@@@@ LOOK LIKE GARBAGE DUE TO AN INCORRECT MSA TRANSFER   FC
)@@G@@@E@@@@ FORMAT BEING SELECTED. IF THIS APPEARS TO BE THE CASE,     @E@@@@FD
)@@G@@ THE @MODE COMMAND CAN BE USED TO CHANGE IT AND RAT CAN     @D@@@@ THEN FE
)@@G@@BE RE-EXECUTED WITH THE 'N' OPTION FOR MORE     @]@@@@ DUMPS.     @^@@@@FF
)@@G@@1FUTURE ENHANCEMENTS    @E@@@@ IN THE FUTURE THE PROCESSOR SHOULD BE GIVFG
)@@G@@EN THE CAPABILITY @E@@@@ OF DUMPING A REQUESTED NUMBER OF BLOCKS. IT SHOFH
)@@G@@ULD ALSO    @F@@@@ ALLOW THE USER TO SELECT THE CHARACTER DUMPS THAT HE FI
)@@G@@DESIRES.    @ @@@@ AND, IT SHOULD BE REUSABLE.  ___^+)HIS IS USUALLY    FJ

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@PB
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@           AXR$    @]@@@B          . @]@@@B          . PC
)@@G@@@G@@@B          . THIS SUBROUTINE CAN BE USED TO RETRIEVE FILE OR USE NAPD
)@@G@@ME    @C@@@B          . INFORMATION FROM THE USER'S PCT.    @]@@@B      PE
)@@G@@    . @F@@@B          . REGISTERS USED, AND NOT SAVED, ARE X11, AND A0 TPF
)@@G@@HRU A5@]@@@B          . @C@@@B          . THE SUBROUTINE IS CALLED VIA LPG
)@@G@@MJ X11@C@@@B          . AND ALL RETURNS ARE VIA   J    0,X11@]@@@B      PH
)@@G@@    . @B@@@B          . THERE ARE 6 ENTRY POINTS:     @E@@@B          . PI
)@@G@@BASPCT - WHICH BASES THE PCT AND MUST BE CALLED @E@@@B          .       PJ
)@@G@@   ONLY ONCE BEFORE ANY OTHER CALL IS MADE@E@@@B          . GT1STF - WHIPK
)@@G@@CH RETURNS FILE INFORMATION FOR THE @B@@@B          .          FIRST FILPL
)@@G@@E IN THE PCT@E@@@B          . GTNXTF - WHICH RETURNS FILE INFORMATION FOPM
)@@G@@R THE @B@@@B          .          NEXT FILE IN THE PCT @E@@@B          . PN
)@@G@@GTCURF - WHICH RETURNS FILE INFORMATION FOR THE @C@@@B          .       PO
)@@G@@   'CURRENT' FILE IN THE PCT  @E@@@B          . GT1STU - WHICH RETURNS TPP
)@@G@@HE FIRST USE NAME FOR   @A@@@B          .          A GIVEN FILE   @E@@@BPQ
)@@G@@          . GTNXTU - WHICH RETURNS THE NEXT USE NAME FOR    @A@@@B      PR
)@@G@@    .          A GIVEN FILE   @@@@@B@]@@@B          . @C@@@B          . PS
)@@G@@BASPCT DOES NOT NEED ANY PARAMETERS @A@@@B          . AND DESTROYS REGISPT
)@@G@@TER A0@]@@@B          . @D@@@B          . ALL OTHER ROUTINES EXPECT A0 TPU
)@@G@@O CONTAIN   @C@@@B          . THE ADDRESS OF A PARAMETER LIST.    @]@@@BPV
)@@G@@          . @D@@@B          . GT1STF, GTNXTF, AND GTCURF EXPECT THE     PW
)@@G@@@D@@@B          . PARAMETER LIST TO CONTAIN 7 ADDRESSES,    @B@@@B      PX
)@@G@@    . THESE ARE THE ADDRESSES OF    @C@@@B          .   A 2 WD AREA FOR PY
)@@G@@FILE QUALIFIER    @B@@@B          .   A 2 WD AREA FOR FILE NAME   @B@@@BPZ
)@@G@@          .   A 1 WD AREA FOR F-CYCLE     @C@@@B          .   A 1 WD AREQA
)@@G@@A FOR FILE ASG OPTIONS  @F@@@B          .   A 1 WD AREA FOR A MASS STORAQB
)@@G@@GE FILE ITEM ADDRESS    @C@@@B          .   A 1 WD AREA FOR A NAME ITEM QC
)@@G@@FLAG  @D@@@B          .   A 1 WD AREA FOR A RELATIVE F-CYCLE FLAG @]@@@BQD
)@@G@@          . @E@@@B          . GT1STU AND GTNXTU EXPECT THE PARAMETER LISQE
)@@G@@T     @A@@@B          . TO CONTAIN 2 ADDRESSES, @ @@@B          . THE ADQF
)@@G@@DRESS OF    @F@@@B          .   A 1 WD AREA FOR A MASS STORAGE FILE ITEMQG
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @C@@@B          .   A 2 WD AREA FOR FILE USE NAME     @]@@@BQH
)@@G@@          . @F@@@B          . CALLS TO ANY ROUTINE EXCEPT BASCPT REQUIREQI
)@@G@@ THAT THE   @ @@@B          . PCT IS BASED.     @]@@@B          . @D@@@BQJ
)@@G@@          . AT LEAST ONE CALL TO GT1STF MUST PRECEDE  @B@@@B          . QK
)@@G@@THE CALLS TO GTNXTF OR GTCURF.@]@@@B          . @E@@@B          . CALLS QL
)@@G@@TO GT1STF, GTNXTF AND GTCURF WILL RETURN  @F@@@B          . A VALUE OF 0QM
)@@G@@ IN THE MASS STORAGE FILE ITEM ADDRESS    @B@@@B          . FIELD IF NO QN
)@@G@@FILE CAN BE FOUND.@]@@@B          . @H@@@B          . IF A FILE IS FOUNDQO
)@@G@@, ITS QUALIFIER, NAME, F-CYCLE, ASG OPTIONS,    @F@@@B          . AND MAQP
)@@G@@SS STORAGE FILE ITEM ADDRESS WILL BE RETURNED.  @F@@@B          . IF THEQQ
)@@G@@ FILE IS NOT ASSIGNED, IE. IT IS A NAME ITEM,   @C@@@B          . THE NAQR
)@@G@@ME ITEM FLAG WILL BE SET TO 1.@E@@@B          . IF THE FILE IS ASSIGNED,QS
)@@G@@ THE NAME ITEM FLAG WILL@ @@@B          . BE CLEARED (0).   @]@@@B      QT
)@@G@@    . @F@@@B          . IF THE FILE IS ASSIGNED USING A RELATIVE F-CYCLEQU
)@@G@@,     @F@@@B          . THE RELATIVE F-CYCLE FLAG WILL BE SET TO 1 AND TQV
)@@G@@HE    @G@@@B          . RELATIVE F-CYCLE WILL BE RETURNED IN THE F-CYCLEQW
)@@G@@ FIELD.     @F@@@B          . IF THE FILE IS ASSIGNED WITH AN ABSOLUTE FQX
)@@G@@-CYCLE ONLY,@F@@@B          . THE RELATIVE F-CYCLE FLAG WILL BE CLEARED QY
)@@G@@(0) AND     @D@@@B          . THE ABSOLUTE F-CYCLE WILL BE RETURNED.    QZ
)@@G@@@]@@@B          . @E@@@B          . CALLS TO GT1STU MUST BE PRECEDED BY RA
)@@G@@A CALL TO   @E@@@B          . GT1STF, GTNXTF OR GTCURF, WHICH WILL RETURRB
)@@G@@N     @E@@@B          . THE MASS STORAGE FILE ITEM ADDRESS OF A FILE    RC
)@@G@@@F@@@B          . WHICH GT1STU NEEDS TO FIND A FILE'S FIRST USE NAME.   RD
)@@G@@@]@@@B          . @E@@@B          . CALLS TO GTNXTU MUST BE PRECEDED BY RE
)@@G@@A CALL TO   @ @@@B          . GT1STU OR GTNXTU. @]@@@B          . @E@@@BRF
)@@G@@          . IF A FILE HAS NO USE NAMES GT1STU WILL RETURN   @F@@@B      RG
)@@G@@    . A 0 VALUE IN THE MASS STORAGE FILE ITEM ADDRESS FIELD.@F@@@B      RH
)@@G@@    . IF ALL OF THE USE NAMES FOR A FILE HAVE BEEN RETURNED,@F@@@B      RI
)@@G@@    . GTNXTU WILL RETURN A 0 VALUE IN THE MASS STORAGE FILE @A@@@B      RJ
)@@G@@    . ITEM ADDRESS FIELD.     @[@@@ $(0)  @A@@@ BASPCT*   LXI,U     A0,2RK
)@@G@@*/15+PCTBD$ @E@@@           LBJ       A0,$+1            . BASE PCT AS DBRL
)@@G@@ANK   @^@@@C          L,U       A0,1@I@@@C          ANU       A0,A0     RM
)@@G@@        . RESET FIXED OVERFLOW TOGGLE TO 0 (1108)     @G@@@C          DIRN
)@@G@@        A0,A1             . CREATE DIVIDE FAULT IF 1100/80  @F@@@C      RO
)@@G@@    JNDF      NOT80             . NO DIVIDE FAULT, ITS AN 8 @E@@@C      RP
)@@G@@    L         A0,(RPCTA$+0241)  . GET PCTNAM ADDR     @F@@@C          J RQ
)@@G@@        OUT               . SKIP NEXT ADDR LOAD FOR 8 @G@D@C          L RR
)@@G@@        A0,((RPCTA$-1)+0241)    . GET PCTNAM ADDR (FOR 1108)@G@@@DNOT80 RS
)@@G@@    L         A0,((RPCTA$-1)+0241)    . GET PCTNAM ADDR (FOR 1108)@F@@@CRT
)@@G@@OUT       S         A0,FRSTPCT        . SAVE IT FOR LATER CALLS   @^@A@ RU
)@@G@@          SLJ       TON$@ @A@           SLJ       TOFF$     @E@@@       RV
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @^@@@ CURPCT    RERW
)@@G@@S       1   @^@@@CFRSTPCT   RES       1   @^@@@ FNMLST    RES       1   RX
)@@G@@@^@@@ FNMCUR    RES       1   @^@@@ FCURFL    +         0   @^@@@ CURDSPRY
)@@G@@    RES       1   @^@@@ CURPCTU   RES       1   @^@@@ CURDSPU   RES     RZ
)@@G@@  1   @^@@@ HALF      RES       1   @]@@@ GT1STF*     @E@C@  .        L SA
)@@G@@        A1,(RPCTA$+0241)  . GET ADDR OF PCTNAM  @G@C@           L       SB
)@@G@@  A1,((RPCTA$-1)+0241)             . GET PCTNAM ADDR  @D@@@C          L SC
)@@G@@        A1,FRSTPCT        . GET FIRST ADDR@F@@@           TNZ       FCURSD
)@@G@@FL            . CHECK IF CURRENT FILE REQ @E@@@           SZ        FNMLSE
)@@G@@ST            . NOT CURREN FILE REQ.@G@@@ ALOOP     S         A1,CURPCT SF
)@@G@@        . SAVE PCTNAM ADDR FOR GTNXTF CALL@G@@@           SZ        A5  SG
)@@G@@              . ZERO ENTRIES CHECKED COUNTER    @E@@@ ELOOP     L,U     SH
)@@G@@  A3,3              . 3 WDS PER ENTRY     @G@@@           MSI       A3,ASI
)@@G@@5             . MULTIPLY BY # ENTRIES CHECKED   @E@@@           A,H2    SJ
)@@G@@  A3,A1             . ADD PCTNAM ADDR     @D@@@           A,U       A3,1SK
)@@G@@              . ADD 1 MORE    @F@@@           A,U       A5,1            SL
)@@G@@  . ADD 1 TO ENTRIES CHECKED  @F@@@           TNZ,T1    2,A3            SM
)@@G@@  . IF 0 FOUND FIRST FILE     @D@@@           J         FOUNDF          SN
)@@G@@  . FOUND A FILE  @G@@@ ENDTST    TE,S3     A5,0,A1           . CHECK IFSO
)@@G@@ MORE ENTRIES IN BLOCK  @F@@@           J         ELOOP             . GOSP
)@@G@@ CHECK OTHER ENTRIES    @F@@@           TNZ,H2    0,A1              . CHSQ
)@@G@@ECK NEXT BLOCK LINK     @E@@@           J         NOMORE            . IFSR
)@@G@@ 0, NO MORE FILES @E@@@           A,H2      A1,0,A1           . ADD CURRSS
)@@G@@ ADDR & LINK@G@@@           J         ALOOP             . GO CHECK NEXT ST
)@@G@@SET OF ENTRIES    @[@@@ FOUNDF@G@@@           TNZ       FCURFL          SU
)@@G@@  . CHECK IF CURRENT FILE REQUEST   @E@@@           J         FOUND2    SV
)@@G@@        . NOT CURRENT FILE REQ@D@@@           L         A4,FNMCUR       SW
)@@G@@  . GET FILE COUNT@F@@@           A,U       A4,1              . ADD 1 FOSX
)@@G@@R FILE JUST FOUND @C@@@           S         A4,FNMCUR         . SAVE IT SY
)@@G@@@F@@@           TE        A4,FNMLST         . IS IT THE ONE WE WANT?    SZ
)@@G@@@F@@@           J         ENDTST            . NOPE, GO LOOK SOME MORE   TA
)@@G@@@E@@@ FOUND2    L         A4,FNMLST         . GET # OF LAST FILE  @F@@@ TB
)@@G@@          TNZ       FCURFL            . CHECK FOR GTCURF CALL FLAG@F@@@ TC
)@@G@@          A,U       A4,1              . ONLY ADD 1 IF GTNXTF CALL @F@@@ TD
)@@G@@          S         A4,FNMLST         . SAVE IT FOR GTCURF CALL   @G@@@ TE
)@@G@@          S         A5,CURDSP         . SAVE POS OF FILE FOR GTNXTF CALLTF
)@@G@@@F@@@           DL        A4,0,A3           . PUT FILE NAME IN A4,A5    TG
)@@G@@@F@@@           DS        A4,*1,A0          . RETURN FILE NAME TO CALLERTH
)@@G@@@F@@@           L,H2      A3,2,A3           . GET LINK TO FILE DESCRP   TI
)@@G@@@E@@@           A         A3,A1             . ADD PCTNAM ADDR     @H@@@ TJ
)@@G@@          S,H2      A3,*4,A0          . RETURN FILE DESCRP ADDR TO CALLETK
)@@G@@R     @E@@@           TZ,T1     1,A3              . IS EQUIP CODE 0?    TL
)@@G@@@F@@@           J         REALF             . NOPE, ITS A REAL FILE     TM
)@@G@@@B@@@           L,U       A4,1              .   @G@@@           S       TN
)@@G@@  A4,*5,A0          . RETURN NAME ITEM FLAG TO CALLER @D@@@           DLTO
)@@G@@        A4,2,A3           . GET QUALIFIER @E@@@           DS        A4,*TP
)@@G@@0,A0          . RETURN TO CALLER    @B@@@           SZ        A4        TQ
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@           S         A4,*3,A0          . RETURN NO ASG TR
)@@G@@OPTS  @D@@@           L,T3      A4,1,A3           . GET ABS FCYCLE@E@@@ TS
)@@G@@          S         A4,*2,A0          . RETURN IT TO CALLER @E@@@       TT
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @B@@@ REALF     SZTU
)@@G@@        A4                .   @F@@@           S         A4,*5,A0        TV
)@@G@@  . RETURN REAL FILE FLAG     @D@@@           L,S4      A4,4,A3         TW
)@@G@@  . GET REL FCYCLE@E@@@           TE,U      A4,040            . IF REL FTX
)@@G@@CYCLE IS 040@G@@@           TNZ       A4                . OR 0, THEN USETY
)@@G@@ ABSOLUTE FCYCLE  @E@@@           J         ABSCYC            . NO, ITS TZ
)@@G@@NOT RELATIVE@^@@@           L,U       A5,1@F@@@           S         A5,*UA
)@@G@@6,A0          . RETURN REL FCYCLE FLAG    @B@@@           TLE,U     A4,0UB
)@@G@@41            .   @ @@@           J         RETCYC    @ @@@           ANUC
)@@G@@,U      A4,040    @ @@@           LN        A4,A4     @ @@@           J UD
)@@G@@        RETCYC    @E@@@ ABSCYC    L,T3      A4,4,A3           . GET ABSOUE
)@@G@@LUTE FCYCLE @F@@@           SZ        *6,A0             . RETURN ABS FCYUF
)@@G@@CLE FLAG    @F@@@ RETCYC    S         A4,*2,A0          . RETURN FCYCLE UG
)@@G@@TO CALLER   @D@@@           L         A4,2,A3           . GET ASG OPTS  UH
)@@G@@@D@@@           S         A4,*3,A0          . RETURN EM     @E@@@       UI
)@@G@@    A,H2      A3,1,A3           . ADD QUALIFIER LINK  @D@@@           DLUJ
)@@G@@        A4,1,A3           . GET QUALIFIER @E@@@           DS        A4,*UK
)@@G@@0,A0          . RETURN IT TO USER   @E@@@           J         0,X11     UL
)@@G@@        . RETURN TO CALLER    @F@@@ NOMORE    SZ        *4,A0           UM
)@@G@@  . RETURN NO FILE FOUND FLAG @E@@@           J         0,X11           UN
)@@G@@  . RETURN TO CALLER    @F@@@ GTNXTF*   L         A1,CURPCT         . GEUO
)@@G@@T LAST FILE PCTNAM ADDR @F@@@           L         A5,CURDSP         . GEUP
)@@G@@T LAST FILE DISPLACEMENT@ @@@           SZ        FCURFL    @F@@@       UQ
)@@G@@    J         ENDTST            . JUMP INTO CHECK ENTRY LOOP@]@@@ GTCURFUR
)@@G@@*     @^@@@           L,U       A4,1@F@@@           S         A4,FCURFL US
)@@G@@        . SET CURRENT FILE FLAG     @F@@@           SZ        FNMCUR    UT
)@@G@@        . SET CUR FILE NUM TO 0     @B@@@           J         GT1STF    UU
)@@G@@        .   @]@@@ GT1STU*     @H@C@           L         A1,((RPCTA$-1)+0UV
)@@G@@241)              . GET ADDR OF PCTNAM    @E@@@C          L         A1,FUW
)@@G@@RSTPCT        . GET ADDR OF PCTNAM  @G@@@ ALOOPU    S         A1,CURPCTUUX
)@@G@@        . SAVE PCTNAM ADDR FOR GTNXTU CALL@E@@@           SZ        A5  UY
)@@G@@              . 0 ENTRIES COUNTER   @F@@@ ELOOPU    L,U       A3,3      UZ
)@@G@@        . 3 WORDS PER FILE ENTRY    @H@@@           MSI       A3,A5     VA
)@@G@@        . MULTIPLY BY NUMBER OF ENTRIES CHECKED @E@@@           A,H2    VB
)@@G@@  A3,A1             . ADD PCTNAM ADDR     @D@@@           A,U       A3,1VC
)@@G@@              . ADD 1 MORE    @E@@@           TNZ,T1    2,A3            VD
)@@G@@  . CHECK IF FILE NAME  @F@@@           J         USEDONE           . ALVE
)@@G@@L DONE WITH USE NAMES   @F@@@           A,U       A5,1              . ADVF
)@@G@@D 1 TO ENTRIES CHECKED  @D@@@           L,H2      A2,2,A3           . GEVG
)@@G@@T LINK ADDR @E@@@           A         A2,A1             . ADD PCTNAM ADDVH
)@@G@@R     @D@@@           S,H2      A2,HALF           . JUST NEED H2  @B@@@ VI
)@@G@@          L,H2      A2,HALF           .   @C@@@           TNE       A2,*VJ
)@@G@@0,A0          . MATCH?  @E@@@           J         FOUNDU            . FOVK
)@@G@@UND A USE NAME    @G@@@ ENDTSTU   TE,S3     A5,0,A1           . CHECK IFVL
)@@G@@ MORE ENTRIES IN BLOCK  @E@@@           J         ELOOPU            . YEVM
)@@G@@S, GO CHECK THEM  @F@@@           TNZ,H2    0,A1              . CHECK NEVN
)@@G@@XT BLOCK LINK     @C@@@           J         USEDONE           . ALL DONEVO
)@@G@@@E@@@           A,H2      A1,0,A1           . ADD CURR ADDR & LINK@G@@@ VP
)@@G@@          J         ALOOPU            . GO CHECK NEXT SET OF ENTRIES    VQ
)@@G@@@H@@@ FOUNDU    S         A5,CURDSPU        . SAVE USE NAME POS FOR GTNXVR
)@@G@@TU CALL     @D@@@           DL        A4,0,A3           . GET USE NAME  VS
)@@G@@@E@@@           DS        A4,*1,A0          . RETURN IT TO CALLER @E@@@ VT
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @F@@@ USEDONVU
)@@G@@E   SZ        *0,A0             . RETURN END FLAG TO CALLER @E@@@       VV
)@@G@@    J         0,X11             . RETURN TO CALLER    @G@@@ GTNXTU*   L VW
)@@G@@        A1,CURPCTU        . GET LAST USE NAME PCTNAM ADDR   @G@@@       VX
)@@G@@    L         A5,CURDSPU        . GET LAST USE NAME DISPLACEMENT  @F@@@ VY
)@@G@@          J         ENDTSTU           . JUMP INTO CHECK ENTRY LOOP@[@@@ VZ
)@@G@@ END  _@@@@@@ @@@B          . PCT IS BASED.     @]@@@B          . @D@@@BWA
)@@G@@          . AT LEAST ONE CALL TO GT1STF MUST PRECEDE  @B@@@B          . WB
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@B.     @ @@@B.         SAVETAPE PROCESSOR  @[@@@B.     WC

)@@G@@@[@@@B.     @G@@@B.         THIS PROCESSOR, WHEN USED IN THE LABELLED TAWE
)@@G@@PE ENVIRONMENT,   @G@@@B.         ALLOWS THE USER TO RETRIEVE THE REEL NWF
)@@G@@UMBERS OF OUTPUT TAPES  @G@@@B.         ASSIGNED TO HIS RUN.  THE OPERATWG
)@@G@@OR IS SUPPLIED WITH ENOUGH    @D@@@B.         INFORMATION TO MAKE A LABEWH
)@@G@@L FOR THE TAPE.   @[@@@B.     @D@@@B.         @SAVETAPE,OPTS FILE,EQT/SEWI

)@@G@@E,TS FILE.  @[@@@B.     @A@@@B.         MODIFIED FEB 77 BY JPS    @D@@@BWO
)@@G@@.         CHANGED TO USE CUSTOMER NUMBER FROM THE     @D@@@B.         PAWP
)@@G@@CHYDERM BUFFER (VIA ENTRY POINT FULCUS)   @D@@@B.         FULCUS IS IN TWQ
)@@G@@HE ISD SYS$*RLIB$ (LIB-90)    @D@@@B.         IF SOURCE IS NEEDED, LOCATWR

)@@G@@ VIA  @B@@@B.         THE TAG ISD EQU 1 AT OUR SITE   @[@@@B.     @C@@@BWT

)@@G@@ALLOW USERS TO GET AN   @A@@@B.         UNLABELED BLANK TAPE.     @[@@@BWW
)@@G@@.     @D@@@D.         MODIFIED APRIL 1982 BY PATRICIA MOELLER     @F@@@DWX
)@@G@@.         CHANGED THE CODE DEALING WITH UNLABELED BLANK TAPES.    @F@@@DWY
)@@G@@.         A TEST WAS ADDED SO THAT THE EXEC LEVEL ID IS CHECKED.  @F@@@DWZ
)@@G@@.         IF THE PROCESSOR IS BEING EXECUTED ON A LEVEL 37 SYSTEM @G@@@DXA
)@@G@@.         THE CODE CHECKS TO SEE IF THE QD2H2AQSVTPJ (ACQUIRE SAVETAPES XB
)@@G@@@G@@@D.         WITH THE 'J' OPTION) BIT IS SET - IF IT IS SET THE REQUEXC
)@@G@@ST    @F@@@D.         IS HONORED, OTHERWISE THE REQUEST IS DENIED.  IF TXD
)@@G@@HE    @G@@@D.         PROCESSOR IS BEING EXECUTED ON ANYTHING OTHER THANXE
)@@G@@ A LEVEL    @C@@@D.         37 SYSTEM "LOOK" PRIVILEGE IS CHECKED.@G@@@DXF
)@@G@@.         ALSO, THE "WREM" MESSAGE (WRONG REEL MESSAGE) WAS ALTERED.    XG
)@@G@@@G@@@D.         ON A LABELED TAPE REQUEST, THE TAPE LABEL IS CHECKED AGAXH
)@@G@@INST  @G@@@D.         THE REEL NUMBER GIVEN BY THE OPERATOR, IF THE REELXI
)@@G@@ NUMBERS    @E@@@D.         DO NOT MATCH THE "WREM" MESSAGE IS SENT.  THXJ
)@@G@@E NEW @F@@@D.         MESSAGE READS, "TAPE LABEL SAYS: XXXX CONTINUE? (YXK
)@@G@@,N)". @[@@@D.     @#@@@B          AXR$    @#@@@B          DEFUNCT$@^@@@BXL
)@@G@@          LIT$      2   @[@@@B$(1). @[@@@B.     @F@@@BAC        EQU     XM
)@@G@@  023                 LOCATION OF ACCOUNT IN PCT@F@@@BASMEQT    EQU     XN
)@@G@@  'U'                 ASSUMED EQUIPMENT TYPE    @H@@@BDES2      EQU     XO

)@@G@@@[@@@B.     @G@@@B.         IF THE TAG 'JOPREST' IS SET NONZERO, ONLY PRXX

)@@G@@TAPE MOUNTED.  IF @H@@@B.         THE REEL NUMBER TYPED IN DISAGREES WITYD
)@@G@@H THE REEL NUMBER RETURNED    @H@@@B.         VIA TSWAP$, THE OPERATOR WYE
)@@G@@ILL BE GIVEN THE OPTION OF CORRECTING     @G@@@B.         HIS KEYED IN RYF
)@@G@@EEL NUMBER OR MOUNTING A CORRECTLY LABELED TAPE.@G@@@B.         THIS TAGYG

)@@G@@POSSIBLE TO CORRECTLY LABEL TAPES.  (ALTHOUGH THERE REMAINS @G@@@B.     YI

)@@G@@.         ENVIRONMENT.  @[@@@B.     @E@@@BILLITERATES EQU     1         YK
)@@G@@          YOU GUESSED IT !    @[@@@B.     @^@@@BP         PROC      2   YL

)@@G@@          SINF      1,5 NOWK            LOOK FOR WRITE KEY  @E@@@B      FO
)@@G@@    SA        A0,KYLOC            SAVE THE WRITE KEY  @E@@@BWKPRS     F$FP
)@@G@@CHAR    '/'                 EDIT LEADING SLASH  @D@@@B          F$MSG   FQ
)@@G@@  KYLOC               EDIT THE KEY  @G@@@BNOWK      LA,U      A0,'&'    FR
)@@G@@          LOAD NORMAL MESSAGE TERMINATOR  @E@@@B          SA,S2     A0,FFS
)@@G@@P$              SET UP PACKET AGAIN @D@@@B          J         0,X8      FT
)@@G@@          RETURN TO CALL@[@@@B.     @E@@@B.         EDIT SLASH IF NO REAFU
)@@G@@D KEY AND WRITE KEY PRESENT   @[@@@B.     @F@@@BNORK      SINF      1,5 FV
)@@G@@NOWK            SEE IF WRITE KEY SUPPLIED @E@@@B          SA        A0,KFW
)@@G@@YLOC            WRITE KEY.  SAVE IT @H@@@B          F$CHAR    '/'       FX
)@@G@@          EDIT SLASH FOR NULL READ KEY FIELD    @E@@@B          J       FY
)@@G@@  WKPRS               GO EDIT WRITE KEY   @[@@@B.     @G@@@B.         ALFZ
)@@G@@LOW ELEMENT NAME TO BE USED AS FILE NAME IF NO FILE NAME    @G@@@B.     GA
)@@G@@    IS SPECIFIED.  HENCE, ASSIGN MAY BE USED FOR THE NORMAL CASE  @H@@@BGB
)@@G@@.         WITHOUT BEING ENTERED IN THE EXEC TABLE, OR REQUIRING THE USERGC
)@@G@@ TO   @C@@@B.         SUPPLY A DOT AFTER THE FILE NAME.     @[@@@B.     GD
)@@G@@@F@@@BNOFN      SINF      1,6 FNERR           LOOK FOR ELEMENT NAME     GE
)@@G@@@E@@@B          DS        A0,FN               SAVE IT AS FILE NAME@G@@@BGF
)@@G@@          F$FD2     .                   FOUND ONE.  EDIT AS FILE NAME   GG
)@@G@@@E@@@B          J         0,X8                RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@BGH
)@@G@@.     @G@@@BNOEQT     LA,U      A0,ASMEQT           LOAD IMPLIED EQUIPMEGI
)@@G@@NT TYPE     @D@@@B          J         EQTED               GO EDIT IT    GJ
)@@G@@@[@@@B.     @E@@@BNOID      DL        A0,('SAVE TAPE   ') LOAD CANNED NAGK
)@@G@@ME    @C@@@B          DS        A0,IDENT            STORE IT@D@@@B      GL
)@@G@@    LA,U      A0,9                LOAD LENGTH   @E@@@B          SA      GM
)@@G@@  A0,IDENTL           STORE FOR EDITING   @F@@@B          J         DEMRGN
)@@G@@TN              PROCESS CONSOLE MESSAGE   @[@@@B.     @G@@@BFNERR     PRGO
)@@G@@INT$    FNEM,FNEL           NO FILE NAME SPECIFIED.  ERROR  @F@@@B      GP
)@@G@@    J         DWNTUBES            GURGLE, GURGLE, GURGLE    @[@@@B.     GQ
)@@G@@@ @@@B.   ASSIGN CONFLICT ERRORS    @[@@@B.     @ @@@BNTERR     PRINT$  GR
)@@G@@  REJM,REJL @D@@@B          PRINT$    NTEM,NTEL           NON TAPE FILE GS
)@@G@@@ @@@B          J         DWNTUBES  @ @@@BMTERR     PRINT$    REJM,REJL GT
)@@G@@@E@@@B          PRINT$    MTEM,MTEL           ANOTHER TAPE MOUNTED@ @@@BGU
)@@G@@          J         DWNTUBES  @[@@@B.     @ @@@B.         PROCESSOR CALLGV
)@@G@@ ERROR@[@@@B.     @F@@@BINFERR    PRINT$    .                   PRINT THGW
)@@G@@E ERROR MESSAGE   @E@@@BDWNTUBES  TZ        DEMAND              CALLED FGX
)@@G@@ROM DEMAND ?@F@@@B          EXIT$     .                   YES.  EXIT GRAGY
)@@G@@CEFULLY     @E@@@B          ABORT$    .                   BATCH.  ZAP THGZ
)@@G@@E RUN @[@@@B.     @C@@@B.         SOLICIT FILE DESCRIPTION FROM DEMAND  HA
)@@G@@@[@@@B.     @F@@@BDEMDSC    TREAD$P   TRDDFP            . ASK USER TO DEHB
)@@G@@SCRIBE FILE @G@@@B          JZ        A0,DEMDSC         . ASK AGAIN IF AHC
)@@G@@NSWER IS NULL     @E@@@B          LXI,U     A0,0                CLEAR FLHD
)@@G@@AG BITS     @E@@@B          MSI,U     A0,6                COMPUTE CHARACHE
)@@G@@TERS  @D@@@B          SA        A0,IDENTL           SAVE LENGTH   @F@@@BHF
)@@G@@          J         DEMRTN              PROCESS REST LIKE BATCH   @[@@@BHG
)@@G@@.     @[@@@B.     @B@@@B.         ASSIGN ERROR STATUS PROCESSING  @[@@@BHH
)@@G@@.     @E@@@BCSFWRN    TP        CSFST               WARNING OR REJECT ? HI
)@@G@@@H@@@B          J         ERRASG              REJECT.  EXAMINE FOR POSSIHJ
)@@G@@BLE WAIT BIT@B@@@B          $IF       LV32              .32 @E@@@B      HK
)@@G@@    LA        A0,CSFST            LOAD CSF$ STATUS    @G@@@B          SAHL
)@@G@@        A0,FITPKT           SET IN FACERR EDITING BUFFER    @G@@@B      HM
)@@G@@    LA,U      A1,FITPKT           LOAD EDITING BUFFER ADDRESS     @G@@@BHN
)@@G@@          RLINK$    'FACR$$'            LINK TO FACILITY ERROR BANK     HO
)@@G@@@#@@@B          $ELSE   @H@@@B          SA        A0,CSFT           PUT HP
)@@G@@STATUS IN ERRPR$ PACKET       . NTW @F@@@B          LA,U      A0,ERRPKT HQ
)@@G@@        GET ERRPR$ PACKET ADDRESS   @D@@@B          ER        ERRPR$    HR
)@@G@@        PUT OUT MESSAGE @#@@@B          $ENDF   @E@@@B          LA      HS
)@@G@@  A0,CSFST            LOAD THE STATUS     @F@@@B          TOP       A0,(HT
)@@G@@BIT(33))        FILE ASSIGNED ALREADY ?   @F@@@B          J         GETFHU
)@@G@@L               NO.  ALLOW OTHER BITS     @^@@@B          $IF       LV32HV
)@@G@@@E@@@B          DL        A0,('$$SAVETAPE$$') LOAD INTERNAL NAME  @#@@@BHW
)@@G@@          $ELSE   @E@@@B          DL        A0,FN             LOAD INTERHX
)@@G@@NAL NAME    @#@@@B          $ENDF   @F@@@B          DS        A0,FITPKT HY
)@@G@@          STORE IN FITEM$ PACKET    @E@@@B          FITEM$    FITPKT,13 HZ
)@@G@@          GET FILE DESCRIPTION@D@@@B          LA,S1     A0,FITPKT+6     IA
)@@G@@    GET EQUIP CODE@E@@@B          TG        A0,O20              IS FILE IB
)@@G@@A TAPE?     @E@@@B          J         NTERR               NOT TAPE - ABOIC
)@@G@@RT    @A@@@B.  ALREADY ASSIGNED FILE IS A TAPE  @E@@@B          TZ      ID
)@@G@@  FITPKT+11           IS TAPE MOUNTED?    @D@@@B          J         MTERIE
)@@G@@R               YES - ABORT   @ @@@B          J         GETFL     @[@@@BIF
)@@G@@.     @E@@@BERRASG    LA        A0,CSFST            LOAD THE STATUS     IG
)@@G@@@D@@@B          TOP       A0,(BIT(18))        WAIT STATUS ? @G@@@B      IH
)@@G@@    J         ASGERP              NO.  EDIT MESSAGE FOR OTHER     @G@@@BII
)@@G@@          TZ        DEMWT               WAITING FOR DEMAND ASSIGN ?     IJ
)@@G@@@F@@@B          J         DSW                 YES.  SKIP DEMAND DIALOG  IK
)@@G@@@D@@@B          TZ        DEMAND              DEMAND RUN ?  @H@@@B      IL
)@@G@@    J         DEMQS               YES.  ASK USER IF HE WANTS TO WAIT    IM
)@@G@@@E@@@BDSW       LA        A0,FIRST            LOAD FIRST TIME FLAG@D@@@BIN
)@@G@@          ANU,U     A0,1                DECREMENT IT  @F@@@B          TNIO
)@@G@@Z       A0                  TIME TO TALK TO OPERATOR ?@H@@@B          LAIP
)@@G@@,U      A1,5                YES.  SET UP TO TALK IN ANOTHER MINUTE@G@@@BIQ
)@@G@@          SA        A1,FIRST            UPDATE FIRST COUNTDOWN QUANTITY IR
)@@G@@@F@@@B          JNZ       A0,NOCON            SKIP OUTPUT IF NOT TIME   IS
)@@G@@@H@@@B          COM$      CONWS,17.           INFORM OPERATOR PROGRAM ISIT
)@@G@@ WAITING    @C@@@B          TNZ       DEMAND              DEMAND ?@E@@@BIU
)@@G@@          J         NOCON               NO.  DON'T PRINT    @F@@@B      IV
)@@G@@    PRINT$    CONWS,CONWSL        TELL DEMAND USER WHAT'S UP@E@@@BNOCON IW
)@@G@@    TWAIT$    10000               WAIT FOR TEN SECONDS@D@@@B          J IX
)@@G@@        NOEXP               TRY AGAIN     @[@@@B.     @H@@@BASGERP.     IY
)@@G@@                                                            . NTW @^@@@BIZ
)@@G@@          $IF       LV32@E@@@B          LA        A0,CSFST            LOJA
)@@G@@AS CSF$ STATUS    @F@@@B          SA        A0,FITPKT           SAVE IN JB
)@@G@@FITEM$ PACKET     @H@@@B          LA,U      A1,FITPKT           LOAD MESJC
)@@G@@SAGE EDITOR BUFFER ADDRESS    @G@@@B          RLINK$    'FACR$$'        JD
)@@G@@    LINK TO FACILITY ERROR BANK     @#@@@B          $ELSE   @H@@@B      JE
)@@G@@    SA        A0,CSFT           SAVE STATUS IN ERRPR$ PACKET      . NTW JF
)@@G@@@F@@@B          LA,U      A0,ERRPKT         GET ERROR$ PACKET ADDRESS   JG
)@@G@@@E@@@B          ER        ERRPR$            PUT OUT ERROR MESSAGE @#@@@BJH
)@@G@@          $ENDF   @D@@@B          J         DWNTUBES            ERROR THJI
)@@G@@E RUN @[@@@B.     @F@@@B.         ERROR NON-PRIVILEGED USER REQUESTING UJJ
)@@G@@NLABELED TAPE     @[@@@B.     @ @@@B          ON        JOPREST   @E@@@BJK
)@@G@@JOPTER    PRINT$    JOPTEM,JOPTEL       PRINT ERROR MESSAGE @E@@@B      JL
)@@G@@    J         DWNTUBES            ERROR OFF CALLER    @ @@@B          OFJM
)@@G@@F       JOPREST   @[@@@B.     @G@@@B.         THIS CODE IS ENTERED WHEN JN
)@@G@@THE REEL NUMBER TYPED IN BY THE     @G@@@B.         OPERATOR DISAGREES WJO
)@@G@@ITH THE REEL NUMBER RETURNED VIA TSWAP$.  @G@@@B.         A MESSAGE IS DJP
)@@G@@ISPLAYED CONTAINING THE REEL NUMBER FROM THE    @G@@@B.         TAPE LABJQ
)@@G@@EL.  THE OPERATOR SHOULD COMPARE THAT REEL NUMBER     @F@@@B.         WIJR
)@@G@@TH THE STICK-ON LABEL AND THE REEL NUMBER HE KEYED IN.@F@@@B.         IFJS
)@@G@@ THE KEYIN WAS WRONG, THE OPERATOR SHOULD ANSWER 'K', @F@@@B.         WHJT
)@@G@@ICH WILL CAUSE THE REEL NUMBER TO BE SOLICITED AGAIN. @G@@@B.         IFJU
)@@G@@ THE TAPE IS IMPROPERLY LABELED, THE OPERATOR SHOULD RESPOND@F@@@B.     JV
)@@G@@    'T', WHICH WILL @FREE AND REASSIGN THE TAPE SO THAT A   @C@@@B.     JW
)@@G@@    CORRECTLY LABELED TAPE MAY BE MOUNTED.@[@@@B.     @A@@@B          ONJX
)@@G@@        ILLITERATES     @F@@@BWRONGREEL F$MSG     WREM                EDJY
)@@G@@IT WRONG REEL MESSAGE   @G@@@B          F$FD1     FN1+2               EDJZ
)@@G@@IT REEL NUMBER FROM LABEL     @E@@@B          F$MSGR    .               KA
)@@G@@    EDIT REST OF MESSAGE@F@@@B          F$COLN    .                   GEKB
)@@G@@T COLUMNS IN MESSAGE    @F@@@B          SA,H1     A0,CONRPKT+1        SEKC
)@@G@@T CHARACTERS TO TYPE    @G@@@B          LA,U      A0,1                LOKD
)@@G@@AD ONE CHARACTER REPLY LENGTH @E@@@B          SA,H1     A0,CONRPKT+2    KE
)@@G@@    SET INPUT LENGTH    @G@@@B          COM$P     CONRPKT           . ASKF
)@@G@@K OPERATOR WHAT'S GOING ON    @D@@@B          F$DT      .               KG
)@@G@@    CLEAR THE LINE@D@@@B          TNZ,H2    CONRPKT             NULL REPKH
)@@G@@LY ?  @F@@@B          J         WREXP               YES.  EXPLAIN ANSWERKI
)@@G@@S     @D@@@B          LA,S1     A0,REPLY            LOAD REPLY    @F@@@BKJ
)@@G@@          TNE,U     A0,'Y'              BAD REEL NO. AN ACCIDENT ?@H@@@BKK
)@@G@@          J         ILASK               YES.  GIVE OPERATOR ANOTHER CHANKL
)@@G@@CE    @E@C@B          NE,U      A0,'T'              BADLY LABELED TAPE ?KM
)@@G@@@E@@@C          TE,U      A0,'N'              BADLY LABELED TAPE ?@H@@@BKN
)@@G@@          J         WREXP               NO.  EXPLAIN HOW TO ANSWER MESSAKO
)@@G@@GE    @E@@@B          F$COPY    8,('@FREE,S     ')  EDIT @FREE COMMAND  KP
)@@G@@@G@@@B          LMJ       X8,EFILE            EDIT FILE NAME ON @FREE COKQ
)@@G@@MMAND @F@@@B          CSF$      FL$                 RELEASE THE CURRENT KR
)@@G@@TAPE  @D@@@B          F$DT      .                   CLEAR THE LINE@F@@@BKS
)@@G@@          J         SPROINK             DO IT ALL OVER AGAIN !    @[@@@BKT
)@@G@@.     @B@@@B.         EXPLAIN HOW TO ANSWER MESSAGE   @[@@@B.     @G@@@BKU
)@@G@@WREXP     COM$      WREXPM,39.          EXPLAIN RESPONSES FOR MESSAGE   KV
)@@G@@@F@@@B          J         WRONGREEL         . PUT OUT THE MESSAGE AGAIN KW
)@@G@@@A@@@B          OFF       ILLITERATES     @[@@@B.     @C@@@B.         ASKX
)@@G@@K DEMAND USER IF HE WANTS TO WAIT   @[@@@B.     @E@@@BDEMQS     TREAD$P KY
)@@G@@  TRDWP             . PUT THE QUESTION    @E@@@B          JZ        A0,DKZ
)@@G@@EMQS            RE-ASK IF NULL REPLY@G@@@B          LA,S1     A0,IDENT  LA
)@@G@@          LOAD FIRST CHARACTER OF REPLY   @D@@@B          TNE,U     A0,'LB
)@@G@@N'              DON'T WAIT ?  @E@@@B          J         DEMAB           LC
)@@G@@    RIGHT.  GIVE UP     @C@@@B          TE,U      A0,'Y'              YELD
)@@G@@S ?   @E@@@B          J         DEMQS               RE-ASK THE QUESTION LE
)@@G@@@H@@@B          SA        A0,DEMWT            THE ANSWER IS YES.  SET DELF
)@@G@@MAND WAITING@E@@@B          J         DSW                 ENTER WAIT LOOLG
)@@G@@P     @[@@@B.     @F@@@BDEMAB     PRINT$    ANP,ANPL            TELL USELH

)@@G@@E NORMALLY FOR DEMAND   @[@@@B$(2). @[@@@B.     @^@@@BFN        'FILENAMLJ
)@@G@@E'    @^@@@BFN1       '$$SAVETAPE$$'@F@@@B          'REEL'              LK

)@@G@@@A@@@@.                              P    @A@@@@.                       TJ
)@@G@@      P     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SCRIPT IS A REWRITE OF A PROTK
)@@G@@GRAM WHICH ONCE EXISTED AT CHI.     @F@@@@. THOSE ALREADY FAMILIAR WITH TL
)@@G@@THE CHI VERSION MAY  SKIP  THIS     @F@@@@. DESCRIPTION;  HOWEVER, THEY TM
)@@G@@WILL PROBABLY RUN INTO PROBLEMS     @F@@@@. SINCE THE USE,  CALLING  SEQTN
)@@G@@UENCE,  INPUT  AND  OUTPUT  ARE     @]@@@@. DIFFERENT.@[@@@@.     @B@@@@TO
)@@G@@. A TYPICAL SCRIPT CALL WOULD LOOK LIKE:  @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         @STP
)@@G@@CRIPT,F LOUISE    @A@@@@.         $HAPPY $BIRTHDAY $LOUISE! @[@@@@.     TQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. WHILE  SOMEWHAT  TRITE,  THIS  WOULD  HAVE  THE  (GENERALLY     TR
)@@G@@@F@@@@. DESIRABLE)  EFFECT  OF  PRODUCING THE WORDS 'HAPPY BIRTHDAY     TS
)@@G@@@F@@@@. LOUISE!' IN ENORMOUS SCRIPT LETTERS  ALONG  THE  LENGTH  OF     TT
)@@G@@@F@@@@. ABOUT  FIVE  PAGES.  THE FIRST LETTER OF EACH WORD WOULD BE     TU
)@@G@@@F@@@@. IN UPPER CASE AS THEY HAVE BEEN PRECEEDED  BY  THE  FORCING     TV
)@@G@@@F@@@@. CHARACTER  ('$')  AND  THE  'F' OPTION WAS SPECIFIED ON THE     TW
)@@G@@@F@@@@. PROCESSOR CALL.  THE LARGE LETTERS WOULD BE COMPOSED OF THE     TX
)@@G@@@F@@@@. LETTERS  'L',  'O',  'U',  'I',  'S',  AND  'E' REPEATED AS     TY
)@@G@@@F@@@@. NECESSARY.  (IF LOUISE HAD NOT  BEEN  PLACED  ON  THE  CALL     TZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. CARD,  THE  DEFAULT  CHARACTER,  '%',  WOULD HAVE BEEN USED     UA
)@@G@@@]@@@@. INSTEAD.) @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE USE OF THE 'F' OPTION SHOULD  UB
)@@G@@BE  RESTRICTED  TO  THOSE     @F@@@@. CALLS  WHICH  CANNOT  PROVIDE UPPEUC
)@@G@@R/LOWER CASE MESSAGES VIA     @F@@@@. THE INPUT MEDIUM.  WITHOUT THE 'F'UD
)@@G@@ OPTION, THE OUTPUT  WILL     @C@@@@. APPEAR EXACTLY AS THE INPUT (ONLY UE
)@@G@@BIGGER).    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE  OTHER  OPTIONS  RELEVANT TO SCRIPT UF
)@@G@@ARE THE 'D' AND 'B'     @F@@@@. OPTIONS WHICH RESULT CORRESPONDINGLY IN UG
)@@G@@'DEMAND' FORMAT AND     @E@@@@. 'BATCH' FORMAT REGARDLESS OF THE ACTUAL UH
)@@G@@MODE OF THE RUN.  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.           UI
)@@G@@                            BOB ELMAN     @E@@@@.                       UJ

)@@G@@AGE   @I@@@@NONCONTIG EQU       2                   BLANK LINES BETWEEN UX
)@@G@@DISCONNECTED LETTERS    @H@@@@NONCON1   EQU       1                   LIUY
)@@G@@NES BETWEEN CONNECTED/NON-CONNECTED @I@@@@SPACE     EQU       15        UZ
)@@G@@          LINES TO LEAVE FOR A SPACE (+NONCONTIG)     @H@@@@L1        EQVA
)@@G@@U       7                   NUMBER OF BITS IN STARTING POS FIELD  @G@@@@VB
)@@G@@L2        EQU       6                   NUMBER OF BITS IN LENGTH FIELD  VC
)@@G@@@I@@@@MAXHGT    EQU       76                  MAXIMUM PRINT POSITIONS FOVD
)@@G@@R A CHARACTER     @H@@@@.                   THE FOLLOWING VALUE IS THE DVE
)@@G@@EFAULT IF NO PARAMENTERS IS   @H@@@@.                   SPECIFIED IN THEVF
)@@G@@ PROGRAM NAME FIELD OF THE PROCESSOR CALL.@G@@@@CHAR      '%%%%%%%%%%%%'VG
)@@G@@     DOUBLE WORD (ROTATED) TO BUILD CHARACTERS  @H@@@@NOHDG     'H,N . 'VH
)@@G@@                      PRINT CONTROL USED TO DISABLE HEADINGS@ @@@@NOHDGLVI
)@@G@@    EQU       $-NOHDG   @F@@@@SPACES    ' '                           WOVJ
)@@G@@RD OF FIELDATA SPACES   @#@@@@          ASCII   @I@@@@FORCE     EQU     VK
)@@G@@  '$'                 FORCING CHARACTER IF 'F' OPTION PRESENT.    @I@@@@VL
)@@G@@UOMASM    EQU       1                   1 IF ASSEMBLY VIA UNIVERSITY OF VM
)@@G@@MD @ASM     @F@@@@. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . VN
)@@G@@. . . . . . @[@@@@/     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. REGISTER UTILIZATION IS RATHVO
)@@G@@ER TIGHT THROUGHOUT THIS ROUTINE.   @C@@@@. IN GENERAL, REGISTERS ARE USVP
)@@G@@ED AS FOLLOWS:    @A@@@@.         A0,A1     GENERAL USE.    @B@@@@.     VQ
)@@G@@    A2        OUTPUT WORD POINTER.  @C@@@@.         A3        OUTPUT CHAVR
)@@G@@RACTER POINTER.   @E@@@@.         A4        PROGRAM TYPE (DEMAND/DEADLINVS
)@@G@@E/BATCH).   @D@@@@.         A5        PROCESSOR CALL (OR @XQT) OPTIONS. VT
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         A6        BIT 0 SET IF CURRENT CHARACTER IS NON-CONTIGUOVU
)@@G@@US TYPE.    @H@@@@.                   BIT 1 SET IF PREVIOUS CHARACTER ISVV
)@@G@@ NON-CONTIGUOUS TYPE.   @H@@@@.         A7        = A6 UNTIL FIRST LINE VW
)@@G@@OF CURRENT CHAR IS PRINTED, THEN 0. @B@@@@.         A8        CURRENT INVX
)@@G@@PUT WORD.   @C@@@@.         A9        CURRENT INPUT CHARACTER.    @G@@@@VY
)@@G@@.         A10,A11   DOUBLE WORD FROM CURRENT CHARACTER'S SEGMENT TABLE. VZ
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         A12       GENERAL USE.    @E@@@@.         A13       PENDWA
)@@G@@ING INTER-CHARACTER SPACING COUNT.  @E@@@@.         A16       INPUT IMAGWB
)@@G@@E LENGTH IN (ASCII) WORDS.    @A@@@@.         R1        GENERAL USE.    WC
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         R2        SEGMENT PART COUNTER IN CURRENT DOUBLE WORD (AWD
)@@G@@10, A11)    @F@@@@.         R3        TOTAL SEGMENT COUNT FOR CURRENT CHWE
)@@G@@ARACTER.    @F@@@@.         R7        CHARACTER COUNT WITHIN CURRENT INPWF
)@@G@@UT WORD.    @F@@@@.         R14       LAST CHARACTER WAS THE FORCING CHAWG
)@@G@@RACTER FLAG.@ @@@@.         R15       UNUSED.   @B@@@@.         X1      WH
)@@G@@  INPUT WORD POINTER.   @H@@@@.         X2        DOUBLE WORD POINTER TOWI
)@@G@@ CURRENT CHARACTERS SEGMENT TABLE.  @D@@@@.         X9        CURRENT PRWJ
)@@G@@INT POSITION ON LINE.   @A@@@@.         X11       GENERAL USE.    @[@@@@WK
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@$(1),START. @G@@@@          AREAD$    INBUF,EXIT          REWL
)@@G@@AD SOME MORE INFOR OR DATA    @C@@@@          TOP       A0,(BIT(31))    WM
)@@G@@    INFOR?  @F@@@@          J         HAVECARD            NO -- PROCESS WN
)@@G@@AS DATA CARD@F@@@@          L,U       R1,1,A0             GET INFOR LENGWO
)@@G@@TH PLUS ONE @G@@@@          L,U       A0,010106           MAGIC CONSTANTWP
)@@G@@ FOR PROGRAM NAME @E@@@@          L         A1,(1,INBUF0)       START ATWQ
)@@G@@ INBUF-1    @F@@@@          SE,H1     A0,,*A1             FIND THAT CONTWR
)@@G@@ROL WORD    @G@@@@          J         START               READ ANOTHER CWS
)@@G@@ARD IF NOT FOUND  @F@@@@          SZ        INBUF0              CLEAR OUWT
)@@G@@T PREFIX WORD     @H@@@@          TNZ       R1                  IS THE PWU
)@@G@@ROGRAM NAME IN THE BUFFER?    @H@@@@          S,H1      A0,INBUF0       WV
)@@G@@    NO -- SET UP FOR FIND ON NEXT READ    @H@@@@          DL        A0,,WW
)@@G@@A1              GET THE PROGRAM NAME (IF PRESENT)     @I@@@@          DSWX
)@@G@@C       A0,36               SHIFT SO FIRST CHAR WILL COME OUT RIGHT.    WY
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TZ        R1                  WAS IT PRESENT?     @G@@@@WZ
)@@G@@          DS        A0,CHAR             YES -- OVERSTORE DEFAULT VALUE  XA
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         START               READ SOME MORE@[@@@@.     XB
)@@G@@@G@@@@HAVECARD  LUF       A15,A0              PUT INPUT CARD LENGTH INTOXC
)@@G@@ A16  @E@@@@          PRTCN$    NOHDG,NOHDGL        TURN OFF ANY HEADINGXD
)@@G@@@G@@@@          PMARG$    STDPAG,0,0          REQUEST CONTINUOUS PRINTINXE
)@@G@@G     @F@@@@          TEP       A5,(BIT(34))        IS PRINT$ BREAKPOINTXF
)@@G@@ED?   @H@@@@          L,U       A4,6                YES -- USE BATCH DEFXG
)@@G@@AULTS FORM HERE ON@F@@@@          L         X1,(1,0)            X1 IS INXH
)@@G@@PUT WORD POINTER  @G@@@@          L,U       R14                 R14 IS FXI
)@@G@@ORCE NEXT CHARACTER FLAG@H@@@@          L,U       A6,1                A6XJ
)@@G@@ IS NON-CONTIGUOUS CHARACTER FLAG   @F@@@@          L,U       A13,2*NONCXK
)@@G@@ONTIG     SET UP INITIAL SPACING    @G@@@@          J         ELOOP1    XL
)@@G@@          ENTER AT END OF CHARACTER LOOP  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. TOP OF NEWXM
)@@G@@ INPUT CHARACTER LOOP   @G@@@@LOOP      JGD       R14,HAVECHAR        SKXN
)@@G@@IP SPECIAL TESTS WHEN FORCING @G@@@@          TOP       A5,OPT(OPTION('FXO
)@@G@@')) SHOULD FORCING CHARS BE HONORED?@G@@@@          J         HAVECHAR  XP
)@@G@@          NO -- PROCESS ANY CHARACTER     @H@@@@          TNE,U     A9,FXQ
)@@G@@ORCE            YES -- IS THIS THE FORCING CHARACTER? @F@@@@          L,XR
)@@G@@U       R14,2               YES -- SET FORCING FLAG   @E@@@@          JGXS
)@@G@@D       R14,ELOOP           PROCESS CHARACTER   @G@@@@          TG,U    XT
)@@G@@  A9,'A'              IS THIS AN UPPER CASE ALPHA?    @ @@@@          TGXU
)@@G@@,U      A9,'Z'+1  @E@@@@          J         HAVECHAR            NO -- LEXV
)@@G@@AVE IT ALONE@G@@@@          A,U       A9,040              YES -- CONVERTXW
)@@G@@ IT TO LOWER CASE @G@@@@HAVECHAR  TG,U      A9,' '+1            IS IT A XX
)@@G@@PRINTABLE CHARACTER?    @C@@@@          J         PRINTCHAR           YEXY
)@@G@@S     @D@@@@          TNE,U     A9,' '              IS IT A SPACE?@F@@@@XZ
)@@G@@ISSPACE   A,U       A13,SPACE           LEAVE 'SPACE' BLANK LINES @H@@@@YA
)@@G@@          L,U       A6,1                SET NON-CONTIGUOUS CHARACTER FLAYB
)@@G@@G     @F@@@@          J         ELOOP               GO GET NEXT CHARACTEYC
)@@G@@R     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@PRINTCHAR L         A0,A9               COPY THEYD
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @D@@@@          TNZ,H1    TAB,A0              IS IT DEFINED?YE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          J         ISSPACE             NO -- TREAT AS A SPACE    YF
)@@G@@@I@@@@          LSSL      A6,1                ADVANCE HISTORY OF NON-CONYG
)@@G@@TIGUOUS CHARS     @G@@@@          TG,U      A9,'A'+040          IS THIS YH
)@@G@@A LOWER CASE ALPHA?     @A@@@@          TG,U      A9,'Z'+040+1    @H@@@@YI
)@@G@@          A,U       A6,1                NO -- SET CURRENT IS NON-CONTIGUYJ
)@@G@@OUS   @I@@@@          AND,U     A6,3                A7 NON-0 IF CURR OR YK
)@@G@@PREV NON-CONTIGUOUS     @E@@@@          L         A6,A7               COYL
)@@G@@PY BACK THE VALUE @E@@@@          L,H1      R3,TAB,A0           GET SEGMYM
)@@G@@ENT COUNT   @F@@@@          L,H2      X2,TAB,A0           GET FIRST SEGMYN
)@@G@@ENT ADDRESS @H@@@@          L,U       R2                  REMAINING SEG YO
)@@G@@CNT IN CURR DBL WORD    @F@@@@          LXI,U     X2,2                DOYP
)@@G@@UBLE WORD INCREMENT     @G@@@@          L,U       X9                  IMYQ
)@@G@@POSSIBLY LOW CURRENT COLUMN   @E@@@@          J         ENXTSEG         YR
)@@G@@    ENTER AT END OF LOOP@[@@@@.     @ @@@@. PROCESS NEW SEGMENT LOOP    YS
)@@G@@@F@@@@NXTSEG    JGD       R2,SEG1             ANOTHER SEGMENT AVAILABLE?YT
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DL        A10,,*X2            NO -- GET SOME@G@@@@SEGS2 YU
)@@G@@    EQU       72/(L1+L2)          SEGMENTS IN FIRST DOUBLE WORD   @H@@@@YV
)@@G@@          L,U       R2,SEGS2*2+(73-L1>SEGS2*(L1+L2))-1 # OF PIECES LEFT YW
)@@G@@- 1   @G@@@@SEG1      LDSC      A10,L1              EXTRACT STARTING COLYX
)@@G@@UMN PORTION @A@@@@          AND,U     A11,BS(L1-1)    @F@@@@          TLYY
)@@G@@E       A12,X9              SEGMENT ON CURRENT LINE?  @H@@@@          LMYZ
)@@G@@J       A1,PRINT            NO -- CLOSE OUT THE PREVIOUS LINE     @G@@@@ZA
)@@G@@          LUF       A2,A12              SET UP TO COMPUTE STORE INDEX   ZB
)@@G@@@F@@@@          TOP       A5,OPT(OPTION('D')) DEMAND FORMAT REQUESTED?  ZC
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TNE,U     A4,4                NO -- DEMAND RUN?   @G@@@@ZD
)@@G@@          TEP       A5,OPT(OPTION('B')) YES -- DEMAND ALLOWED AT ALL?   ZE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          A,U       A3,(OUTBUFL-MAXHGT)/2 NO -- FORMAT AS BATCH   ZF
)@@G@@@J@@@@          AN,U      A3,1                COMPENSATE FOR 1ST PRINT PZG
)@@G@@OSITION NUMBERED AS 1   @F@@@@          DI,U      A2,6                COZH
)@@G@@NVERT TO WORD/CHAR INDEX@F@@@@          AH        A3,(1,EXTAB)        SEZI
)@@G@@T UP FOR EXECUTE TABLE  @^@@@@          LXI,U     A2,1@F@@@@          L ZJ
)@@G@@        X9,A12              COPY REQUESTED POSITION   @F@@@@          JGZK
)@@G@@D       R2,SEG3             SEGMENT LENGTH AVAILABLE? @F@@@@          DLZL
)@@G@@        A10,,*X2            NO -- GET SOME SEGMENTS   @F@@@@          L,ZM
)@@G@@U       R2,(72-L2)/(L1+L2)*2 NUMBER OF PIECES - 1     @E@@@@SEG3      LDZN
)@@G@@SC      A10,L2              EXTRACT LENGTH FIELD@A@@@@          AND,U   ZO
)@@G@@  A11,BS(L2-1)    @F@@@@          A         X9,A12              COMPUTE ZP
)@@G@@ENDING POSITION   @E@@@@          J         EINNER              ENTER ATZQ
)@@G@@ END OF LOOP@[@@@@.     @G@@@@INNER     DL        A0,CHAR             GEZR
)@@G@@T NEXT CHARACTER TO FILL WITH @F@@@@          LDSC      A0,6            ZS
)@@G@@    ROTATE CHARACTERS ONE     @F@@@@          DS        A0,CHAR         ZT
)@@G@@    PUT BACK ROTATED GROUP    @G@@@@          AND,U     A0,BS(5)        ZU
)@@G@@    EXTRACT THE CURRENT CHARACTER   @E@@@@          JZ        A1,INNER  ZV
)@@G@@          DON'T USE ZEROS     @E@@@@          TNE,U     A1,5            ZW
)@@G@@    OR FIELDATA SPACES  @ @@@@          J         INNER     @E@@@@      ZX
)@@G@@    EX        0,*A3               STORE ONE CHARACTER @F@@@@EINNER    JGZY
)@@G@@D       A12,INNER           LOOP FOR ALL OF SEGMENT   @I@@@@ENXTSEG   JGZZ
)@@G@@D       R3,NXTSEG           LOOP FOR ALL SEGMENTS OF THIS CHARACTER     AA
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LMJ       A1,PRINT            PRINT LAST LINE OF CHARACTAB
)@@G@@ER    @H@@@@ELOOP     JGD       R7,SHIFT            ANY MORE INPUT CHARSAC
)@@G@@ IN CURRENT WORD? @G@@@@ELOOP1    L,U       R7,3                NO -- COAD
)@@G@@UNT FOR NEXT WORD - 1   @D@@@@          L         A8,INBUF,*X1        GEAE
)@@G@@T NEXT WORD @E@@@@          JGD       A16,SHIFT           ANY MORE WORDSAF
)@@G@@?     @F@@@@          PRINT$    ,,SPACE             EJECT ONE EXTRA SPACAG
)@@G@@E     @E@@@@          PMARG$    STDPAG,STDTOP,STDBOT RESTORE THE MARGINSAH
)@@G@@@E@@@@          PLINE$    .                   EJECT TO TOP OF FORM@D@@@@AI
)@@G@@EXIT      EXIT$     .                   RETURN TO EXEC@[@@@@.     @F@@@@AJ
)@@G@@SHIFT     LSSC      A8,9                GET THE NEXT CHARACTER    @F@@@@AK
)@@G@@          AND,U     A8,BS(6)            STRIP DOWN TO 7 BIT ASCII @D@@@@AL
)@@G@@          J         LOOP                GO PROCESS IT @[@@@@.     @[@@@@AM
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE IS USED TO PRINT EACH LIAN
)@@G@@NE.   @#@@@@. AT ENTRANCE:    @G@@@@.         IF A7 IS NON-ZERO THEN NONAO
)@@G@@-CONTIGUOUS PRINTING IS REQUESTED   @C@@@@.         A13 IS SPACING COUNTAP
)@@G@@ (BEFORE PRINT)   @B@@@@.         OUTBUF CONTAINS THE PRINT IMAGE @[@@@@AQ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@@PRINT     JZ        A7,CONTIG           IS THE OUTPUT CONTINAR
)@@G@@UOUS? @B@@@@          ON        1-(NONCONTIG=NONCON1) @G@@@@          TEAS
)@@G@@P,U     A7,3                BOTH CHARS ARE NON-CONTIGUOUS?  @H@@@@      AT
)@@G@@    AN,XU     A13,NONCONTIG-NONCON1 NO -- ONLY ONE IS NON-CONTIGUOUS    AU
)@@G@@@B@@@@          OFF       1-(NONCONTIG=NONCON1) @E@@@@          L,U     AV
)@@G@@  A7                  CLEAR FOR NEXT TIME @E@@@@          A,U       A13,AW
)@@G@@NONCONTIG       ADD ON EXTRA SPACING@G@@@@          J         CONTIG    AX
)@@G@@          ENTER AT END OF SPACING LOOP    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@PRINT1    PRAY
)@@G@@INT$    ,,1                 DO NOT OPTIMIZE THIS LOOP @E@@@@CONTIG    JGAZ
)@@G@@D       A13,PRINT1          SPACE AS NECESSARY  @B@@@@          PRINT$  BA
)@@G@@  OUTBUF,OUTBUFL//6     @F@@@@          L,U       A2,A13              GEBB
)@@G@@T ADDRESS OF SPACES     @E@@@@          L         A13,SPACES          GEBC
)@@G@@T FIELDATA SPACES @^@@@@          LXI,U     A0,1@F@@@@          L,U     BD
)@@G@@  R1,OUTBUFL//6       SET UP FOR BLOCK TRANSFER @E@@@@          BT      BE
)@@G@@  A0,,*A2             CLEAR THE LINE IMAGE@G@@@@          L,U       A13 BF
)@@G@@                CLEAR SPACING PENDING COUNT     @C@@@@          J       BG
)@@G@@  0,A1                RETURN  @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. FOLLOWING BH
)@@G@@IS THE EXECUTE REMOTE TABLE USED FOR STORING INTO THE @F@@@@. OUTPUT BUFBI
)@@G@@FER, OUTBUF.  A3 IS THE (ABSOLUTE) TABLE INDEX, A2 IS @F@@@@. THE OUTPUTBJ
)@@G@@ WORD INDEX AND A1 IS THE FIELDATA CHARACTER TO STORE.@[@@@@.     @A@@@@BK
)@@G@@EXTAB1    S,S6      A1,OUTBUF,*A2   @ @@@@          LMJ       A3,,A3    BL
)@@G@@@[@@@@EXTAB.@C@@@@I         DO        5 , S,S1+1-I A1,OUTBUF,A2   @ @@@@BM
)@@G@@          LMJ       A3,EXTAB1 @[@@@@/$(3).@C@@@@OUTBUF    REZ       OUTBBN
)@@G@@UFL//6,050505050505     @I@@@@INBUF0    +         0                   PRBO
)@@G@@EFIX - MUST IMMEDIATELY PRECEED INBUF     @^@@@@INBUF     RES       64  BP
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     BQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@$(5). @G@@@@. A SEGMENT IS DEFINED AS A CONSECUTIVE STRING OF ONE BR
)@@G@@OR MORE CHARACTERS@F@@@@. USED TO BUILD THE OUTPUT CHARACTERS.  SEGMENTSBS
)@@G@@ ARE DEFINED BY A @G@@@@. STARTING PRINTER COLUMN NUMBER [1:76] AND A SEBT
)@@G@@GMENT LENGTH [1:63].    @G@@@@. ANY SEGMENT WHICH WOULD OVERLAY ITS IMMEBU
)@@G@@DIATE PREDECESSOR OR BEGIN    @G@@@@. TO THE LEFT OF ITS IMMEDIATE PREDEBV
)@@G@@CESSOR IS AUTOMATICALLY STARTED     @#@@@@. ON A NEW LINE.  @[@@@@.     BW
)@@G@@@F@@@@. THE LIST OF SEGMENTS USED TO MAKE UP A CHARACTER ARE PACKED INTOBX
)@@G@@@F@@@@. QUADRUPLE WORDS CONSISTING OF A MAXIMUM OF ELEVEN PAIRS (WITH   BY
)@@G@@@F@@@@. 7 BITS PER STARTING COLUMN AND 6 BITS PER LENGTH) FOLLOWED BY   BZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. AN UNUSED BIT.  THIS UNUSUAL PACKING IS THE JOB OF THE PROC 'Z'.CA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @G@@@@. THE FOLLOWING DEFINITIONS ARE REPEATED AS A WARNING CB
)@@G@@TO ANYONE WHO     @G@@@@. MAY TRY TO CHANGE THE OTHER SET (AT THE BEGINNCC
)@@G@@ING OF THE ELEMENT).    @F@@@@. LOGIC CHANGES AND MAJOR CHANGES TO THE PCD
)@@G@@ROC 'Z' ARE REQUIRED IF @A@@@@. THESE TWO VALUES ARE MODIFIED.    @H@@@@CE
)@@G@@L1        EQU       7                   LENGTH IN BITS OF STARTING POS FCF
)@@G@@IELD  @G@@@@L2        EQU       6                   LENGTH IN BITS OF LECG
)@@G@@NGTH FIELD  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THE FOLLOWING SUBSCRIPTED FORMS ARE SELECH
)@@G@@CTED BY THE 'DO' LOOP IN@F@@@@. THE PROC 'Z' TO GENERATE SOME SEGMENTS (CI
)@@G@@OR SEGMENT PIECES).     @F@@@@F(0)      FORM      L2,L1,L2,L1,L2,L1,L2,LCJ
)@@G@@1,L2,L1,L2,72-5*L1-6*L2 @D@@@@F(2)      FORM      L1,L2,L1,L2,L1,L2,L1,LCK
)@@G@@2,L1,L2,L1  @D@@@@F(1)      FORM      L2,L1,L2,L1,L2,36-2*(L1+L2)-L2    CL
)@@G@@@C@@@@F(3)      FORM      L1,L2,L1,L2,36-2*(L1+L2)    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@CM
)@@G@@. THE NUMBER 11 (WHICH OCCURS THROUGHOUT THE PROC Z) IS DERIVED FROM    CN
)@@G@@@G@@@@. THE FACT THAT THERE ARE 11 FULL SEGMENTS (OF 13 BITS) IN A QUADRCO
)@@G@@UPLE  @]@@@@. WORD.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@Z*        PROC      *255@F@@@@CP
)@@G@@C         EQU       Z(1,1)+040*Z(1,*1)  GET ASCII CHARACTER VALUE @E@@@@CQ
)@@G@@          DO        (C<041)++(C>0177) , EQU 09  'E' FLAG    @G@@@@      CR
)@@G@@    DO        (A(C)=0)++(A(C)=(Z-1,$))--1 ,C EQU -1  'D' FLAG!    @ @@@@CS
)@@G@@A*(C)     EQU       +(Z-1,$)  @F@@@@I         DO        (Z-1)*(L1+L2)//7CT
)@@G@@2 , F(2*(I**1)+(11*I/2>Z+1)) ;@F@@@@                    Z(11*I//2-4,2-(ICU
)@@G@@**1)),Z(11*I/2-3,1+(I**1)),;  @F@@@@                    Z(11*I//2-3,2-(ICV
)@@G@@**1)),Z(11*I/2-2,1+(I**1)),;  @F@@@@                    Z(11*I//2-2,2-(ICW
)@@G@@**1)),Z(11*I/2-1,1+(I**1)),;  @F@@@@                    Z(11*I//2-1,2-(ICX
)@@G@@**1)),Z(11*I/2+0,1+(I**1)),;  @F@@@@                    Z(11*I//2+0,2-(ICY
)@@G@@**1)),Z(11*I/2+1,1+(I**1)),;  @B@@@@                    Z(11*I//2+1,2-(ICZ
)@@G@@**1)) @#@@@@          END     @G@@@@ Z 'A'  36,16  33,25  31,31  28,36  DA
)@@G@@27,11  49,17  27,10  55,14  26,9   ;@G@@@@        58,13  26,8   61,12  2DB

)@@G@@    END       START     ___  ;  28,6   27,8   26,10  26,10  27,8   28,6 QM
)@@G@@@G@A@^ Z  '#' 43,4   43,7   54,4   43,7   54,7   38,12  54,7   38,23  38QN
)@@G@@,28  ;@G@@@@ Z '#'  43,4   43,7   54,4   43,7   *[S@@@*SDFF*@#@@@@SCRIPTQO
)@@G@@ PROCESSOR  @]@@@[OPTION P,ON @]@[@@1DESCRIPTION@]@@@[SPACE 3     @E@@@@QP
)@@G@@ SCRIPT IS A REWRITE OF A PROGRAM WHICH ONCE EXISTED AT CHI.@E@@@@ THOSEQQ
)@@G@@ ALREADY FAMILIAR WITH THE CHI VERSION MAY  SKIP  THIS@E@@@@ DESCRIPTIONQR
)@@G@@;  HOWEVER, THEY WILL PROBABLY RUN INTO PROBLEMS@E@@@@ SINCE THE USE,  CQS
)@@G@@ALLING  SEQUENCE,  INPUT  AND  OUTPUT  ARE@]@@@@ DIFFERENT. @@@@@@@B@@@@QT
)@@G@@ A TYPICAL SCRIPT CALL WOULD LOOK LIKE:   @@@@@@@ @@@@         @SCRIPT,FQU
)@@G@@ LOUISE     @A@@@@         $HAPPY $BIRTHDAY $LOUISE!  @@@@@@@E@@@@ WHILEQV
)@@G@@  SOMEWHAT  TRITE,  THIS  WOULD  HAVE  THE  (GENERALLY@E@@@@ DESIRABLE) QW
)@@G@@ EFFECT  OF  PRODUCING THE WORDS 'HAPPY BIRTHDAY@E@@@@ LOUISE!' IN ENORMQX
)@@G@@OUS SCRIPT LETTERS  ALONG  THE  LENGTH  OF@E@@@@ ABOUT  FIVE  PAGES.  THQY
)@@G@@E FIRST LETTER OF EACH WORD WOULD BE@E@@@@ IN UPPER CASE AS THEY HAVE BEQZ
)@@G@@EN PRECEEDED  BY  THE  FORCING@E@@@@ CHARACTER  ('$')  AND  THE  'F' OPTRA
)@@G@@ION WAS SPECIFIED ON THE@E@@@@ PROCESSOR CALL.  THE LARGE LETTERS WOULD RB
)@@G@@BE COMPOSED OF THE@E@@@@ LETTERS  'L',  'O',  'U',  'I',  'S',  AND  'E'RC
)@@G@@ REPEATED AS@E@@@@ NECESSARY.  (IF LOUISE HAD NOT  BEEN  PLACED  ON  THERD
)@@G@@  CALL@E@@@@ CARD,  THE  DEFAULT  CHARACTER,  '%',  WOULD HAVE BEEN USEDRE
)@@G@@@]@@@@ INSTEAD.)  @@@@@@@E@@@@ THE USE OF THE 'F' OPTION SHOULD  BE  RESRF
)@@G@@TRICTED  TO  THOSE@E@@@@ CALLS  WHICH  CANNOT  PROVIDE UPPER/LOWER CASE RG
)@@G@@MESSAGES VIA@E@@@@ THE INPUT MEDIUM.  WITHOUT THE 'F' OPTION, THE OUTPUTRH
)@@G@@  WILL@C@@@@ APPEAR EXACTLY AS THE INPUT (ONLY BIGGER).     @@@@@@@E@@@@RI
)@@G@@ THE  OTHER  OPTIONS  RELEVANT TO SCRIPT ARE THE 'D' AND 'B'@E@@@@ OPTIORJ
)@@G@@NS WHICH RESULT CORRESPONDINGLY IN 'DEMAND' FORMAT AND@E@@@@ 'BATCH' FORRK
)@@G@@MAT REGARDLESS OF THE ACTUAL MODE OF THE RUN.   ___ OF THE RUN.   ___ OFRL

)@@G@@    AXR$.     WALTER GILBERT UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND ADMINISTRATION@^@@@@MY
)@@G@@C         'SORTF 2.6   '@^@@@@          RES       25  @F@@@@RECSIZ    +0MZ
)@@G@@.                           RECORD SIZE, CHARACTERS   @E@@@@NREC      +0NA
)@@G@@.                           NUMBER OF RECORDS   @E@@@@START     L       NB
)@@G@@  A0,(0102,C)         . PRINT SIGN-ON LINE@ @@@@          ER        PRINNC
)@@G@@T$.   @G@@@@          L,U       A0,C.               GET @SORTF IMAGE IN ND
)@@G@@INFOR FORMAT@ @@@@          ER        READ$.    @E@@@@          L       NE
)@@G@@  A0,C.               PICKUP OPTIONS WORD @G@@@@          LSSL      A0,3NF
)@@G@@.               SHIFT 'X' OPTION INTO POSITION 5@H@@@@          S,S1    NG
)@@G@@  A0,WB.              STORE 'X' OPTION INTO SIGN POSITION   @H@@@@      NH
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,010106.          LOOK FOR ELEMENT NAME IN 1ST SUBFIELD NI
)@@G@@@ @@@@          LMJ       X11,FIND. @I@@@@          J         TRY12.    NJ
)@@G@@          NOT, FOUND, LOOK FOR A FILE NAME INSTEAD    @I@@@@FLD1      LMNK
)@@G@@J       X11,CVB.            CHECK & CONV FIELD FROM FIELDATA DECIMAL    NL
)@@G@@@I@@@@          S         A3,NREC.            TO BINARY. THIS IS 'NUMBERNM
)@@G@@ OF RECORDS'.     @H@@@@          L,U       A0,010206.          LOOK FORNN
)@@G@@ ELEMENT NAME IN 2ND SUBFIELD @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,FIND. @H@@@@NO
)@@G@@          J         TRY22.              NOT FOUND, MAY LOOK LIKE FILE NANP
)@@G@@ME    @I@@@@          LMJ       X11,CVB.            CONVERT FROM FIELDATNQ
)@@G@@A DECIMAL TO BINARY     @H@@@@          S         A3,RECSIZ.          THNR
)@@G@@IS IS THE RECORD SIZE, CHAR OR WORDS@I@@@@          L,U       A0,010207.NS
)@@G@@          LOOK FOR VERSION NAME. IF IT STARTS WITH    @I@@@@          LMNT
)@@G@@J       X11,FIND.           'W', ASSUME RECORD SIZE GIVEN IN WORDS,     NU
)@@G@@@H@@@@          J         ENDSCN.             OTHERWISE, ASSUME IT IS GINV
)@@G@@VEN IN CHAR.@E@@@@CH        SSL       A0,30.              ISOLATE 1ST LENW
)@@G@@TTER  @D@@@@          TE,U      A0,'W'.             IS IT A 'W'?  @H@@@@NX
)@@G@@          J         ENDSCN.             NO, ASSUME SIZE GIVEN IN CHARACTNY
)@@G@@ERS   @G@@@@          L         A1,RECSIZ.          CONVERT FROM WORDS TNZ
)@@G@@O CHARACTERS@ @@@@          MSI,U     A1,6.     @ @@@@          S       OA
)@@G@@  A1,RECSIZ.@G@@@@ENDSCN    LMJ       X11,SORTF.          LINK UP WITH @OB
)@@G@@ASG-CARD GENERATOR@F@@@@          +NREC.                        USE A FOOC
)@@G@@RTRAN LINKAGE     @#@@@@          +RECSIZ.@I@@@@WB        +0,'WJG'.     OD
)@@G@@                FLAG TO RECOGNIZE THIS CALL BY. SIGN = X    @C@@@@      OE
)@@G@@    ER        EXIT$.              DONE.   @H@@@@TRY12     L,U       A0,0OF
)@@G@@10102           LOOK FOR A FILE NAME IN 1ST SUBFIELD  @ @@@@          LMOG
)@@G@@J       X11,FIND. @E@@@@          J         ERR1.               NOT FOUNOH
)@@G@@D, ERROR!   @E@@@@          J         FLD1.               FOUND, ALL IS OI
)@@G@@OK.   @H@@@@TRY22     L,U       A0,010202.          LOOK FOR A FILE NAMEOJ
)@@G@@ IN 2ND SUBFIELD  @ @@@@          LMJ       X11,FIND. @F@@@@          J OK
)@@G@@        ERR1.               TWO STRIKES AND YER OUT.  @E@@@@          LMOL
)@@G@@J       X11,CVB.            CONVERT TO BINARY   @F@@@@          S       OM
)@@G@@  A3,RECSIZ.          THIS IS THE RECORD SIZE   @I@@@@          L,U     ON
)@@G@@  A0,010203.          SINCE RECSIZ WAS FILE NAME,  TYPE (CHAR     @H@@@@OO
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,FIND.             OR WORDS) WILL LOOK LIKE A REAOP
)@@G@@D KEY.@I@@@@          J         ENDSCN.             NO 'READ-KEY' FIELD OQ
)@@G@@GIVEN, ASSUME WORDS     @H@@@@          J         CH.                 'ROR
)@@G@@EAD-KEY' FIELD GIVEN, LOOK FOR A 'W'@C@@@@ERR1      L         A0,(0200+EOS
)@@G@@MSG-MSG,MSG).     @F@@@@          ER        PRINT$.             PRINT ANOT
)@@G@@ ERROR MESSAGE.   @ @@@@          ER        ERR$.     @D@@@@MSG       'IOU
)@@G@@LLEGAL OR MISSING FIELD ON @SORTF CARD'.  @[@@@@EMSG. @I@@@@FIND      L OV
)@@G@@        A1,(1,1).           SEARCH INFOR TABLE FOR PARTICULAR FIELD     OW
)@@G@@@ @@@@          J         FINDB.    @F@@@@FINDA     A,S6      A1,C-1,A1.OX
)@@G@@          ADD IN WORD COUNT, 1 OR 2 @G@@@@FINDB     TNZ       C,A1.     OY
)@@G@@          LOOK FOR END OF INFOR IMAGE     @G@@@@          J         0,X1OZ
)@@G@@1.              END FOUND, TAKE 'NO-FIND' EXIT. @F@@@@          TE,H1   PA
)@@G@@  A0,C,*A1.           IS THIS THE RIGHT FIELD?  @G@@@@          J       PB
)@@G@@  FINDA.              NOT FOUND YET, LOOK FURTHER.    @H@@@@          L,PC
)@@G@@S6      A0,C-1,A1.          FOUND, GET FIELD LENGTH, 1 OR 2 WORDS @I@@@@PD
)@@G@@          TE,U      A0,1.               DECIDE WHETHER TO PAD WITH BLANKPE
)@@G@@S OR NOT    @ @@@@          J         FINDC.    @D@@@@          L       PF
)@@G@@  A0,C,A1.            LOAD FIELD.   @F@@@@          L         A1,('     PG
)@@G@@ ').      PAD  WITH A WORD OF BLANKS@C@@@@          J         1,X11.    PH
)@@G@@          RETURN  @D@@@@FINDC     DL        A0,C,A1.            LOAD FIEPI
)@@G@@LD    @G@@@@          LXM,U     A1,050505.          FORCE LAST 3 CHARACTPJ
)@@G@@ERS BLANK   @ @@@@          J         1,X11.    @I@@@@CVB       SZ      PK
)@@G@@  A3.                 CONVERT LEFT JUSTIFIED FIELDATA DECIMAL     @H@@@@PL
)@@G@@CVBA      LDSC      A0,6.                  NUMBER IN A0 & A1 TO BINARY IPM
)@@G@@N A3  @E@@@@          AND,U     A1,077.             ISOLATE CHARACTER   PN
)@@G@@@D@@@@          TNE,U     A2,5.               IS IT A BLANK?@D@@@@      PO
)@@G@@    J         0,X11.              YES, DONE.    @G@@@@          AN,U    PP
)@@G@@  A2,060.             NO, CONVERT DIGIT TO BINARY     @E@@@@          JNPQ
)@@G@@        A2,ERR1.            ERROR IF NOT 0 - 9  @ @@@@          TG,U    PR
)@@G@@  A2,10.    @ @@@@          J         ERR1.     @ @@@@          MSI,U   PS
)@@G@@  A3,10.    @ @@@@          A         A3,A2.    @E@@@@          J       PT
)@@G@@  CVBA.               GET NEXT DIGIT.     @F@@@@          END       STARPU
)@@G@@T.              WALTER GILBERT 8/4/71     ___@@^  CVBA.               GEPV
)@@G@@T NEXT DIGIT.     @F@@@@          END       STAR*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@SORTF PW
)@@G@@@#@@@@1@SORTF PROCESSOR @F@@@@      @SORTF IS A PROCESSOR DESIGNED TO ASPX
)@@G@@SIGN THE MOST EFFICIENT @C@@@@ SORT FILES FOR A PARTICULAR SORT.  THE CAPY
)@@G@@LL IS:@[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@                 @SORTF<,OPTIONS>   NREC,RECSIZ<PZ
)@@G@@/W>   @[@@@@SPACE @C@@@@ WHERE    NREC = NUMBER OF RECORDS TO BE SORTED QA
)@@G@@@F@@@@        RECSIZ = SIZE OF EACH RECORD, IN CHARACTERS.  IF A '/W'   QB
)@@G@@@E@@@@                 FOLLOWS THE RECSIZ, THEN SIZE IS IN WORDS. @[@@@@QC
)@@G@@SPACE @F@@@@ THE ONLY MEANINGFUL OPTION IS 'X', WHICH CAUSES SORTF TO JUQD
)@@G@@ST    @F@@@@ PRINT OUT THE SORT FILE ASSIGN IMAGES, AND NOT TO ASSIGN THQE
)@@G@@EM.   @#@@@@1SORTF SUBROUTINE @F@@@@      SORTF ALSO EXISTS AS A SUBROUTQF
)@@G@@INE CALLABLE FROM FORTRAN-V   @^@@@@ PROGRAMS.  THE CALL IS:@[@@@@SPACE QG
)@@G@@@B@@@@                 CALL SORTF(NREC,NCHAR)   @[@@@@SPACE @G@@@@ WHEREQH
)@@G@@ 'NREC' IS THE NUMBER OF RECORDS EXPECTED, AND 'NCHAR' IS THE     @A@@@@QI
)@@G@@ NUMBER OF CHARACTERS PER RECORD.   @[@@@@SPACE @D@@@@ FROM AN ASSEMBLY QJ
)@@G@@LANGUAGE PROGRAM, THE CALL WOULD BE:@[@@@@SPACE @A@@@@                 LQK
)@@G@@MJ    X11,SORTF   @B@@@@                 +      <ADDR OF NREC>    @B@@@@QL
)@@G@@                 +      <ADDR OF NCHAR>   @ @@@@                 +      QM
)@@G@@0     @A@@@@                 <NORMAL RETURN>    ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@QN
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@QO
