)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@FS
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         TPF PROCFT
)@@G@@ESSOR @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.                                       JOHN WALFU
)@@G@@KER   AUGUST 1973 @[@@@@.     %H@@@@-5                                  FV
)@@G@@                                    . TM82@H@@[@.         MODIFIED SEPT FW
)@@G@@82 BY T. MAHOOD TO USE ER ERRPR$                . TM82@H@@[@.         INFX
)@@G@@STEAD OF RLINK$ FACR$ WHICH IS NOT SUPPORTED                . TM82@H@@[@FY
)@@G@@.         IN EXEC LEVEL 37                                              FZ
)@@G@@. TM82@H@@[@.                                                           GA
)@@G@@            . TM82@F@@@@.         THIS PROCESSOR ENABLES THE USER TO DEFGB
)@@G@@INE A 'TPF' FILE  @H@@@@.         USED IN PLACE OF THE ASSUMED FILE TPF$GC
)@@G@@.  THE PROCESSOR IS CALLED    @ @@@@.         WITH THE STATEMENT: @[@@@@GD
)@@G@@.     @^@@@@.         @TPF FILE.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         WHERE 'FGE
)@@G@@ILE' MAY BE THE FULL SPECIFICATION ALLOWED FOR FILES. @G@@@@.         IFGF
)@@G@@ THE SPECIFICATION CONSISTS OF ONLY A FILE NAME, THE PERIOD @G@@@@.     GG
)@@G@@    MAY BE OMITTED.  IF THE FILE IS CURRENTLY ASSIGNED TO THE RUN,@H@@@@GH
)@@G@@.         THE USE NAME 'TPF$' WILL BE ATTACHED TO THE FILE AND THE PROCEGI
)@@G@@SSOR  @H@@@@.         WILL COMPLETE.  IF THE FILE IS NOT ASSIGNED, IT WIGJ
)@@G@@LL BE DYNAMICALLY @I@@@@.         ASSIGNED WITH THE 'A' AND 'X' OPTIONS.GK
)@@G@@  THE PROCESSOR WILL WAIT IF THE    @G@@@@.         FILE IS NOT AVAILABLGL
)@@G@@E.  IF THE FILE NAME PARAMETER IS OMITTED,@G@@@@.         A FILE CALLED GM
)@@G@@'PROGFILE$' WILL BE USED.  IF NO FILE WITH THE  @H@@@@.         SPECIFIEGN
)@@G@@D NAME EXISTS, A NEW FILE WILL BE CREATED.  THIS ACTION     @H@@@@.     GO
)@@G@@    WILL BE OVERRIDDEN BY THE 'A' OPTION ON THE TPF STATEMENT, WHICH    GP
)@@G@@@H@@@@.         WILL CAUSE AN ERROR MESSAGE IF THE DESIRED FILE DOES NOTGQ
)@@G@@ EXIST.     @G@@@@.         IF TPF IS CREATING A FILE, THE 'P' OPTION WIGR
)@@G@@LL MAKE THAT FILE @#@@@@.         PUBLIC. @[@@@@.     $]@@@@-25   @@@@@@GS
)@@G@@@G@@@@.         THE 'T' OPTION ALLOWS ASSIGNING OR RE-ASSIGNING A TEMPORGT
)@@G@@ARY   @G@@@@.         TPF$ FILE. THIS CAN BE USEFUL WHEN WORKING IN A CAGU
)@@G@@TALOGUED    @G@@@@.         FILE AND THEN, WHEN THROUGH, GOING BACK TO AGV
)@@G@@ TEMPORARY FILE.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         IT IS ALSO POSSIBLE TO SPEGW
)@@G@@CIFY OTHER THAN DEFAULT FOR THE     @G@@@@.         MAX GRANULE SIZE. THGX
)@@G@@IS CAN BE DONE FOR A TEMPORARY FILE BY    @G@@@@.         SPECIFYING THEGY
)@@G@@ SIZE AS THE FIRST ELEMENT ON THE CALL CARD.    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.     GZ
)@@G@@    IE.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         @TPF,T 5000   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@HA
)@@G@@.         THIS WILL FREE THE CURRENT TPF$ AND ASSIGN A NEW ONE WITH     HB
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         A MAX TRACK COUNT OF 5000.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         FOHC
)@@G@@R CATALOGUED FILES, THE MAX TRACK COUNT CAN BE SEPCIFIED    @B@@@@.     HD
)@@G@@    AS THE SECOND ELEMENT NAME.     @[@@@@.     @#@@@@.         IE.     HE
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @^@@@@.         @TPF FILE,5000@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         THHF
)@@G@@IS WILL ASSIGN (OR CATALOG) THE FILE, 'FILE', WITH    @A@@@@.         A HG
)@@G@@MAX TRACK COUNT OF 5000.@[@@@@.     @#@@@@          AXR$    @#@@@@      HH
)@@G@@    DEFUNCT$@#@@@@          ELT$    @^@@@@          LIT$      2   @[@@@@HI
)@@G@@$(1). @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PCF       TNE,U     A4,4                DEMAND RHJ
)@@G@@UN ?  @F@@@@          SA        A4,DEMAND           YES.  SET DEMAND FLAHK
)@@G@@G     @F@@@@          LA        A0,(INFL,INFOR)     LOAD INFOR BUFFER ADHL
)@@G@@DRESS @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,RINF$           READ IN INFOR TABLE HM
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         INFERR              INFOR ERROR   @[@@@@.     HN
)@@G@@@A@@@@.         ** START FUDGE CODE **    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@.         THHO
)@@G@@IS CODE DOES A @FREE TPF$ BEFORE DOING THE REST OF THE @TPF @F@@@@.     HP
)@@G@@    PROCESSING.  THIS IS NECESSARY BECAUSE THERE IS A DANGER@F@@@@.     HQ
)@@G@@    IN HAVING AN INTERNAL NAME AND EXTERNAL NAME THE SAME,  @G@@@@.     HR
)@@G@@    DESPITE THE EXPLICIT STATEMENT IN THE PRM THAT THIS WORKS.    @F@@@@HS
)@@G@@.         IF YOU HAVE TPF$ ASSIGNED, A USE NAME ATTACHED TO TPF$  @A@@@@HT
)@@G@@.         AND EXECUTE THE SEQUENCE: @[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         IF YOU HHU
)@@G@@AVE TPF$ ATTACHED AS A USE NAME TO AN EXTERNAL FILE NAME    @G@@@@.     HV
)@@G@@    AND YOU STILL HAVE TPF$ ASSIGNED, AND YOU DO THE SEQUENCE:    @^@@@@HW
)@@G@@.         @ELT,UL   ELT1@^@@@@.         @ADD ELT2     @H@@@@.         THHX
)@@G@@EN THE REST OF THE UPDATED SOURCE AFTER ELEMENT ELT2 IS CLOSED    @H@@@@HY
)@@G@@.         IS WRITTEN INTO THE TEMP FILE TPF$, NOT THE EXTERNAL FILE ATTAHZ
)@@G@@CHED  @H@@@@.         TO THE USE NAME TPF$.  THIS DOES NOT OCCUR IF TPF$IA
)@@G@@ IS NOT ASSIGNED  @F@@@@.         AS A TEMPORARY FILE.  THIS IS BECAUSE IB
)@@G@@THE EXEC COMPUTES @G@@@@.         AN 'INDEX' ON THE FIRST REFERENCE TO AIC
)@@G@@ FILE, AND ON LATER     @F@@@@.         REFERENCES USING THE SAME PACKETID
)@@G@@, SIMPLY CHECKS IF THE  @F@@@@.         ENTRY THE INDEX POINTS TO HAS THIE
)@@G@@E SAME INTERNAL NAME AS @F@@@@.         THE FILE.  THE PROBLEM IS THAT IIF
)@@G@@F THE PCT IS SHUFFLED BY@F@@@@.         DYNAMIC ASSIGNS AND FREE'S, AND IG
)@@G@@YOU HAVE TWO FILES WITH @F@@@@.         THE SAME NAME ASSIGNED, ONE MAY IH
)@@G@@SHIFT INTO THE INDEX    @G@@@@.         POSITION OF THE OTHER, AND I/O WII
)@@G@@ILL GO TO THE WRONG FILE.     @[@@@@.     @E@@@@.         (THE 'Z' OPTIOIJ
)@@G@@N WILL KEEP IT FROM HAPPENING).     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          LA      IK
)@@G@@  A0,INFOR            LOAD OPTIONS  @H@@@@          JB        A0,NOFUFR IL
)@@G@@          SKIP FUDGE FREE IF 'Z' OPTION IS ON   @F@@@@          FITEM$  IM
)@@G@@  FITPKT,9            GET ASSIGNMENT INFORMATION@E@@@@          TNZ,S1  IN
)@@G@@  FITPKT+6            IS FILE ASSIGNED ?  @H@@@@          J         NOFUIO
)@@G@@FR              NO.  DON'T NEED REDUNDUNDUNDANT FREE !@F@@@@          CSIP
)@@G@@F$      ('@FREE TPF$. '),2  FREE THE TEMP FILE TPF$   @]@@@@NOFUFR    . IQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@.         ** END FUDGE CODE **$]@@@@-72   @@@@@@@D@@@@          LAIR
)@@G@@        A0,INFOR            LOAD OPTIONS  @D@@@@          TOP,U     A0,OIS
)@@G@@PTION('T')      'T' OPTION SET@E@@@@          J         NOTEMP          IT
)@@G@@    NOPE. SKIP THIS     @E@@@@          F$COPY    12,('@ASG,T TPF$.') COIU
)@@G@@PY ASSIGN IMAGE   @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,1                CHECK FOIV
)@@G@@R FIELD ONE @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,SELT$           READ IN FIRST IW
)@@G@@FIELD @E@@@@          J         ASGIT               JUMP IF NOT THERE   IX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          F$MSG     (',///& ')          COPY STATIC PART OF IMAGE IY
)@@G@@@D@@@@          F$COPY    6,ENAME             COPY SIZE     @D@@@@      IZ
)@@G@@    J         ASGIT               GO ASSIGN IT  @D@@@@NOTEMP.           JA
)@@G@@                      NO OP HERE    @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,2      JB
)@@G@@          LOAD FOR FIELD TWO  @G@@@@          LMJ       X11,SELT$       JC
)@@G@@    LOOK FOR POSSIBLE SIZE SPEC     @E@@@@          J         NOSPC2    JD
)@@G@@          JUMP IF NONE THERE  @D@@@@          LA        A0,ENAME        JE
)@@G@@    LOAD SIZE SPEC@D@@@@          SA        A0,INSIZE           SAVE SIZJF
)@@G@@E SPEC@]@@@@NOSPC2.     @E@@@@          LA,U      A0,1                LOJG
)@@G@@OK FOR FIELD ONE  @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,SELT$           BUILD ELJH
)@@G@@T$ FOR FIELD 1    @H@@@@          J         CANPCF              NO FIELDJI
)@@G@@ 1.  USE CANNED FILE NAME     @F@@@@          TNZ       FNL             JJ
)@@G@@    FILE NAME SPECIFIED ?     @G@@@@          J         ELTN            JK
)@@G@@    NO.  TRY TO USE ELEMENT NAME    @E@@@@FUDON     DL        A0,('TPF$ JL
)@@G@@       ') LOAD TPF$ FILE NAME @E@@@@          LMJ       X11,DUSE$       JM
)@@G@@    ATTACH USE NAME     @F@@@@          FITEM$    FITPKT,9            GEJN
)@@G@@T ASSIGNMENT INFORMATION@E@@@@          TZ,S1     FITPKT+6            ISJO
)@@G@@ FILE ASSIGNED ?  @F@@@@          J         ASOK2               YES.  CHJP
)@@G@@ECK EQUIPMENT TYPE%H@@@@-125,125                                        JQ
)@@G@@                        . TM82@E@@[@ASGAX     F$COPY    6,('@ASG,A')    JR
)@@G@@  . COPY ASG,A IMAGE    @D@@[@          LX        A0,INFOR          . GEJS
)@@G@@T OPTIONS   @E@@[@          TEP,U     A0,OPTION('N')    . TEST FOR N OPTJT
)@@G@@ION   @G@@[@          J         SKIPX             . N OPTION, SKIP X-CLUJU
)@@G@@SIVE ASG    @F@@[@          F$CHAR     'X'              . PUT IN THE X, JV
)@@G@@NO N OPTION @D@@[@SKIPX     F$SKIP    1                 . SKIP A SPACE  JW
)@@G@@%@@@@[@D[@@@          LA,U      A0,' '              GET A SPACE   @F@@@@JX
)@@G@@          SA,S2     A0,FP$              SET FMSG$ STOP-ON-SPACE   @G@@@@JY
)@@G@@          F$MSG     FILE$               COPY FILE NAME TO ASSIGN IMAGE  JZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LA,U      A0,'&'              GET AMPERSAND @H@@@@      KA
)@@G@@    SA,S2     A0,FP$              SET STOP CHARACTER BACK TO NORMAL     KB
)@@G@@$]@@@@-88   @@@@@@@E@@@@          TNZ       INSIZE              ANY SIZEKC
)@@G@@ TO ADD IN ?@E@@@@          J         ASGIT               JUMP IF NOT THKD
)@@G@@ERE   @G@@@@          LA,U      A15,1               SAY THAT THERE IS A KE
)@@G@@SIZE SPEC   @E@@@@          F$MSG     (',///& ')          COPY PART OF IKF
)@@G@@MAGE  @D@@@@          F$COPY    6,INSIZE            COPY SIZE     @G@@@@KG
)@@G@@ASGIT     CSF$      FL$                 ASSIGN THE FILE (OR TRY TO)     KH
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SA        A0,CSFST            SAVE STATUS   @F@@@@      KI
)@@G@@    JN        A0,CSFREJ           PROCESS BAD STATUS IF ANY @E@@@@      KJ
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,ASGOK            NO FUNNY BITS ?     %H@@@@-140,142    KK
)@@G@@                                                            . TM82@H@@[@KL
)@@G@@          SA        A0,STAT             . PUT FAC STATUS IN ERRPR$ PKT  KM
)@@G@@. TM82@H@@[@          L,U       A0,ERRPKT           . GET ADDR OF ERRPR$KN
)@@G@@ PKT        . TM82@H@@[@          ER        ERRPR$              . GO DO KO
)@@G@@IT                      . TM82%@@@@#@H[@@@ASGOK     TZ        FIRST     KP
)@@G@@          WAS USE NAME CLEARED BY WAIT LOOP ?   @F@@@@          J       KQ
)@@G@@  ASOK1               NO.  DON'T RE-ATTACH IT   @D@@@@          DL      KR
)@@G@@  A0,('TPF$        ') LOAD USE NAME @F@@@@          LMJ       X11,DUSE$ KS
)@@G@@          ATTACH IT TO THE FILE     @F@@@@ASOK1     FITEM$    FITPKT,9  KT
)@@G@@          GET FILE INFORMATION AGAIN@E@@@@ASOK2     LA,S1     A0,FITPKT+KU
)@@G@@6         LOAD EQUIPMENT TYPE @E@@@@          TLE,U     A0,040          KV
)@@G@@    IS EQUIPMENT TYPE...@D@@@@          TLE,U     A0,030              INKW
)@@G@@ RANGE ?    @G@@@@          J         ILLEQP              NO.  GIVE MESSKX
)@@G@@AGE AND TERMINATE @F@@@@          LA        A0,FITPKT+7         LOAD ASSKY
)@@G@@IGN STATUS BITS   @E@@@@          TEP       A0,(BIT(34))        IS FILE KZ
)@@G@@TEMPORARY ? @H@@@@          J         NOASGI              SKIP ASSIGNMENLA
)@@G@@T INFO IF TEMPORARY     @D@@@@          LA        A0,INFOR            LOLB
)@@G@@AD OPTIONS  @D@@@@          TZ        DEMAND              DEMAND RUN ?  LC
)@@G@@@G@@@@          TEP,U     A0,OPTION('L')      ASSIGN INFO WANTED FOR DEMLD
)@@G@@AND ? @E@@@@          J         EASGI               YES.  GO EDIT IT    LE
)@@G@@@G@@@@          J         NOASGI              INFORMATION NOT WANTED.  SLF
)@@G@@KIP IT@H@@@@EASGI     MSCON$    DRDPKT              READ DIRECTORY MAIN LG
)@@G@@ITEM FOR FILE     @E@@@@          JN        A0,NOASGI           SKIP IF LH
)@@G@@BAD STATUS  @D@@@@          F$DT      .                   CLEAR THE LINELI
)@@G@@@H@@@@          LR,U      R1,7                LOAD LOOP COUNT FOR EQUIPMLJ
)@@G@@ENT TYPES   @F@@@@          LA        A1,(1,0)            LOAD MAIN ITEMLK
)@@G@@ POINTER    @G@@@@          LA,U      A0                  CLEAR GRANULESLL
)@@G@@ ASSIGNED COUNT   @H@@@@          AA,H2     A0,MIBUF+20,*A1     SUM GRANLM
)@@G@@ULES ASSIGNED FOR EACH TYPE   @G@@@@          JGD       R1,$-1          LN
)@@G@@    LOOP FOR ALL EQUIPMENT TYPES    @G@@@@          TP        MIBUF+13  LO
)@@G@@          IS FILE POSITION GRANULARITY ?  @H@@@@          LSSL      A0,6LP
)@@G@@                YES.  CONVERT POSITIONS TO TRACKS     @F@@@@          F$LQ
)@@G@@DECV    .                   EDIT TOTAL TRACKS IN FILE @G@@@@          F$LR
)@@G@@MSG     FASCON              COPY ASSIGN CONFIRMATION MESSAGE@G@@@@      LS
)@@G@@    F$DECV    MIBUF+15,,H2        EDIT ASSIGN COUNT FOR SECURITY  @E@@@@LT
)@@G@@          F$MSGR    .                   COPY REST OF MESSAGE@E@@@@      LU
)@@G@@    F$PRT     1                   PRINT ASSIGN MESSAGE@]@@@@NOASGI    . LV
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TNZ       DEMAND              DEMAND CALLER ?     @D@@@@LW
)@@G@@          EXIT$     .                   NO.  EXIT     @F@@@@          PRLX
)@@G@@INT$    ('READY '),1        YES.  ISSUE READY MESSAGE @D@@@@          EXLY
)@@G@@IT$     .                   TERMINATE     @[@@@@.     @A@@@@.         PRLZ
)@@G@@OCESS CSF$ REJECT STATUS@[@@@@.     @F@@@@CSFREJ    TEP       A0,(BIT(21MA
)@@G@@))        IS 'NOT FOUND' BIT SET ?  @E@@@@          J         NFND      MB
)@@G@@          YES.  PROCESS IT    @H@@@@          TEP,U     A0,BIT(16)      MC
)@@G@@    FILE NOT AVAILABLE FOR EXCLUSIVE ASSG?@E@@@@          J         NOXCMD
)@@G@@L               RIGHT.  WAIT FOR IT @E@@@@          TOP       A0,(BIT(18ME
)@@G@@))        IS WAIT BIT ON ?    @F@@@@          J         FCRJ            MF
)@@G@@    NO.  EDIT ERROR STATUS    @D@@@@NOXCL     TNZ       FIRST           MG
)@@G@@    FIRST TIME ?  @D@@@@          J         NOPW                NO.  JUSMH
)@@G@@T WAIT@[@@@@.     @H@@@@.         IF WE'RE GOING TO CAMP WAITING FOR THEMI
)@@G@@ FILE, WE FREE THE USE NAME   @G@@@@.         AND SET THE FLAG 'FIRST', MJ
)@@G@@WHICH WILL CAUSE THE USE NAME TO BE @H@@@@.         REATTACHED WHEN THE MK
)@@G@@FILE IS SUCCESSFULLY ASSIGNED.  THIS IS DONE    @H@@@@.         SO THAT ML
)@@G@@IF THE USER X-ES THE PROCESSOR WHILE IT IS WAITING, TPF$    @C@@@@.     MM
)@@G@@    WILL BE AS IT WAS WHEN HE ENTERED.    @[@@@@.     @E@@@@          CSMN
)@@G@@F$      FRETUN              FREE THE USE NAME   @F@@@@          SZ      MO
)@@G@@  FIRST               CLEAR FIRST TIME FLAG     @D@@@@          TNZ     MP
)@@G@@  DEMAND              DEMAND MODE ? @D@@@@          J         NOPW      MQ
)@@G@@          NO.  JUST WAIT@F@@@@          PRINT$    FWM,FWL             PRMR
)@@G@@INT 'WAITING...' MESSAGE@E@@@@NOPW      TWAIT$    10000               WAMS
)@@G@@IT FOR TEN SECONDS@D@@@@          J         ASGIT               TRY IT AMT
)@@G@@GAIN  @E@@@@FCRJ      SA        A0,FITPKT           SAVE CSF$ STATUS    MU
)@@G@@%H@@@@-206,207                                                          MV
)@@G@@      . TM82@H@@[@          SA        A0,STAT             . PUT FAC STATMW
)@@G@@US IN ERRPR$ PKT  . TM82@H@@[@          L,U       A0,ERRPKT           . MX
)@@G@@GET ADDR OF ERRPR$ PKT        . TM82@H@@[@          ER        ERRPR$    MY
)@@G@@          . GO DO IT                      . TM82%@@@@]@E[@@@ERROT     CSMZ
)@@G@@F$      FRETUN              FREE THE USE NAME   @D@@@@ERROT1    TNZ     NA
)@@G@@  DEMAND              DEMAND RUN ?  @E@@@@          ABORT$    .         NB
)@@G@@          NO.  ABORT THE RUN  @E@@@@          EXIT$     .               NC
)@@G@@    YES.  EXIT NORMALLY @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.         HANDLE ELEMENT NAME ND
)@@G@@AS FILE NAME@[@@@@.     @E@@@@ELTN      TNZ       ENL                 ANNE
)@@G@@Y ELEMENT NAME ?  @F@@@@          J         BUGGY               NO.  FUNNF
)@@G@@NY SPECIFICATION  @G@@@@          LA        A0,ENL              LOAD LENNG
)@@G@@GTH OF ELEMENT NAME     @F@@@@          SA        A0,FNL              SENH
)@@G@@T AS FILE NAME LENGTH   @E@@@@          DL        A0,ENAME            LONI
)@@G@@AD ELEMENT NAME   @F@@@@          DS        A0,FNAME            USE ELEMNJ
)@@G@@ENT AS FILE NAME  @E@@@@          SZ        FQL                 SET NO QNK
)@@G@@UALIFIER    @D@@@@CLRK      SZ        RKL                 NO READ KEY   NL
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SZ        WKL                 NO WRITE KEY  @D@@@@      NM
)@@G@@    SZ        FCL                 NO F-CYCLE    @F@@@@          J       NN
)@@G@@  FUDON               GO ATTACH USE NAME AGAIN  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.     NO
)@@G@@    ASSIGN CANNED FILE IF NO NAME IS SPECIFIED  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@CANPCFNP
)@@G@@    SZ        FQL                 SET NO QUALIFIER    @F@@@@          DLNQ
)@@G@@        A0,('PROGFILE$   ') LOAD CANNED FILE NAME     @D@@@@          DSNR
)@@G@@        A0,FNAME            SET FILE NAME @F@@@@          LA,U      A0,9NS
)@@G@@                LOAD LENGTH OF CANNED NAME@D@@@@          SA        A0,FNT
)@@G@@NL              SET LENGTH    @F@@@@          SA        A0,CANNED       NU
)@@G@@    SET ASSIGNING CANNED FILE @F@@@@          J         CLRK            NV
)@@G@@    GO CLEAR OTHER FIELDS     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.         PROCESS NO FINNW
)@@G@@D STATUS FROM FILE ASSIGNMENT @[@@@@.     @E@@@@NFND      LA        A0,INX
)@@G@@NFOR            LOAD OPTION BITS    @G@@@@          TEP       A0,(OPTIONNY
)@@G@@('A'))    DID USER SPECIFY 'A' OPTION ?   @G@@@@          J         NFNDNZ
)@@G@@M               YES.  TELL HIM THE BAD NEWS     @E@@@@          F$DT    OA
)@@G@@  .                   CLEAR THE IMAGE     @G@@@@          F$COPY    4,('OB
)@@G@@@CAT  ')        EDIT CONTROL STATEMENT TYPE     @D@@@@          LA      OC
)@@G@@  A1,INFOR            LOAD OPTIONS  %]@@@@-245,248    @F@@[@          ANOD
)@@G@@D       A1,(02002020)     . AND WITH G, V AND P OPTS  @F@@[@          JZOE
)@@G@@        A2,NOGVP          . IF ZERO, NO OPTS MATCH    @D@@[@          F$OF
)@@G@@FD1     (',')             . PUT IN COMMA  @D@@[@          L,U       A0,'OG
)@@G@@ '            . GET A SPACE   @D@@[@          TEP,U     A1,OPTION('P')  OH
)@@G@@  . P OPTION?     @E@@[@          L,U       A0,'P'            . YES, GETOI
)@@G@@ READY TO...@E@@[@          LMJ       X11,FFD1$         . PUT IT IN ASG OJ
)@@G@@IMAGE @D@@[@          L,U       A0,' '            . GET A SPACE   @D@@[@OK
)@@G@@          TEP       A1,(OPTION('G'))  . G OPTION?     @F@@[@          L,OL
)@@G@@U       A0,'G'            . YES, GET READY TO....     @E@@[@          LMOM
)@@G@@J       X11,FFD1$         . PUT IT IN ASG IMAGE @D@@[@          L,U     ON
)@@G@@  A0,' '            . GET A SPACE   @D@@[@          TEP,U     A1,OPTION(OO
)@@G@@'V')    . V OPTION?     @E@@[@          L,U       A0,'V'            . YEOP
)@@G@@S, GET READY TO...@E@@[@          LMJ       X11,FFD1$         . PUT IT IOQ
)@@G@@N ASG IMAGE @E@@[@NOGVP                                 . NO G, V OR P OOR
)@@G@@PTIONS%@@@@^@D[@@@          LA,U      A0,' '              GET A SPACE   OS
)@@G@@@G@@@@          SA,S2     A0,FP$              SET FDIT$ TO STOP AT A SPAOT
)@@G@@CE    %[@@@@-250  @E@@[@          F$FD3                       . EDIT OPTOU
)@@G@@ION FIELD   @E@@@@          F$MSG     FILE$               COPY THE FILE OV
)@@G@@NAME  @E@@@@          F$FD1     (',F2')             EDIT EQUIPMENT TYPE OW
)@@G@@$]@@@@-205  @@@@@@@E@@@@          TNZ       INSIZE              ANY SIZEOX
)@@G@@ SPEC ?     @C@@@@          J         NOSIZE              NOPE.   @E@@@@OY
)@@G@@          F$MSG     ('///   ')          CANNED PART OF IMAGE@D@@@@      OZ
)@@G@@    F$COPY    6,INSIZE            COPY SIZE     @D@@@@NOSIZE.           PA
)@@G@@                      DO NOTHING    @E@@@@          CSF$      FL$       PB
)@@G@@          CATALOGUE THE FILE  @E@@@@          SA        A0,CSFST        PC
)@@G@@    SAVE THE STATUS     @G@@@@          SZ        CANNED              PRPD
)@@G@@OTECT AGAINST INFINITE LOOP   @F@@@@          JN        A0,FCRJ         PE
)@@G@@    PROCESS ERROR CATALOGUING @E@@@@          F$DT      .               PF
)@@G@@    CLEAR THE IMAGE     @D@@@@          F$MSG     FILE$               EDPG
)@@G@@IT FILE NAME@D@@@@          F$FD4     (' CREATED')        EDIT 'CREATED'PH
)@@G@@@C@@@@          F$PRT     1                   PRINT IT@F@@@@          LAPI
)@@G@@,U      A0,'&'              GET NORMAL FMSG$ STOP     @D@@@@          SAPJ
)@@G@@,S2     A0,FP$              RESTORE PACKET@F@@@@          TNZ       FCL PK
)@@G@@                WAS AN F-CYCLE SPECIFIED ?@F@@@@          J         ASGAPL
)@@G@@X               NO.  JUST RE-DO ASSIGN    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.         IFPM
)@@G@@ THE USER SPECIFIED A +1 F-CYCLE, WE CLEAR THE F-CYCLE@G@@@@.         ANPN
)@@G@@D REATTACH THE USE NAME WITHOUT F-CYCLE.  OTHERWISE WE'D    @A@@@@.     PO
)@@G@@    LOOP CREATING +1 F-CYCLES.@[@@@@.     @H@@@@          LA,S1     A0,FPP
)@@G@@CYC             LOAD THE FIRST CHARACTER OF F-CYCLE   @D@@@@          TEPQ
)@@G@@,U      A0,'+'              IS IT A PLUS ?@E@@@@          J         ASGAPR
)@@G@@X               NO.  LET IT STAND   @F@@@@          SZ        FCL       PS
)@@G@@          MARK NO F-CYCLE SPECIFIED @F@@@@          CSF$      FRETUN    PT
)@@G@@          RELEASE CURRENT USE NAME  @G@@@@          J         FUDON     PU
)@@G@@          REDO DYNAMIC USE AND CONTINUE   @[@@@@.     @G@@@@NFNDM     PRPV
)@@G@@INT$    NFM,NFL             PRINT THE NOT FOUND MESSAGE     @D@@@@      PW
)@@G@@    J         ERROT               ERROR OUT     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@.     PX
)@@G@@    PROCESS ILLEGAL EQUIPMENT TYPE  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@ILLEQP    PRINT$  PY
)@@G@@  ILLEQM,ILLEQL       PRINT THE MESSAGE   @D@@@@          J         ERROPZ
)@@G@@T               ERROR OUT     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.         IMPROPER CALL QA
)@@G@@CARD  @[@@@@.     @E@@@@BUGGY     PRINT$    BUGGM,BUGGL         PRINT ERQB
)@@G@@ROR MESSAGE @D@@@@          J         ERROT1              ERROR OFF USERQC
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @E@@@@INFERR    PRINT$    .                   PRINT CANNED MQD
)@@G@@ESSAGE@D@@@@          J         ERROT1              ERROR OFF USER@[@@@@QE
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@$(2). @E@@@@CANNED    EQUF      $,,S1               CANNED FQF
)@@G@@ILE FLAG    @E@@@@FIRST     EQUF      $,,S2               FIRST TIME FLAQG
)@@G@@G     @E@@@@DEMAND    EQUF      $,,S3               DEMAND RUN FLAG     QH
)@@G@@@A@@@@          *         0,1,0,0,0,0     @ @@@@FRETUN    '@FREE,A TPF$ QI
)@@G@@. '   @B@@@@FASCON    ' TRACKS, ASSIGNED & TIMES.&'   @E@@@@ILLEQM    'TQJ
)@@G@@PF FILE MUST BE FASTRAND FORMAT MASS STORAGE.'  @ @@@@ILLEQL    EQU     QK
)@@G@@  $-ILLEQM  @C@@@@BUGGM     'IMPROPER FILE NAME SPECIFICATION.'   @ @@@@QL
)@@G@@BUGGL     EQU       $-BUGGM   @A@@@@FWM       'WAITING FOR FILE...'     QM
)@@G@@@ @@@@FWL       EQU       $-FWM     @A@@@@NFM       'FILE DOES NOT EXISTQN
)@@G@@.'    @ @@@@NFL       EQU       $-NFM     @^@@@@FITPKT    'TPF$        'QO
)@@G@@@^@@@@          RES       7   %H@@@@-315,315                            QP
)@@G@@                                    . TM82@H@@[@.                       QQ
)@@G@@                                                . TM82@H@@[@.         ERQR
)@@G@@ ERRPR$ PACKET                                              . TM82@H@@[@QS
)@@G@@.                                                                       QT
)@@G@@. TM82@H@@[@ERRPKT    040,0,0,0,0,0               . WD 1 OF 3 FOR PKT   QU
)@@G@@            . TM82@H@@[@          +0                          . WORD 2 OQV
)@@G@@F 3 FOR PKT             . TM82@H@@[@          +0                        QW
)@@G@@  . WORD 3 OF 3 FOR PKT             . TM82@H@@[@ET        EQUF      ERRPQX
)@@G@@KT,,S1        . ERROR TYPE 040 = FAC            . TM82@H@@[@STAT      EQQY
)@@G@@UF      ERRPKT+2          . STATUS BITS                     . TM82%@@@@[QZ
)@@G@@@^[@@@INFOR     RES       56  @ @@@@INFL      EQU       $-INFOR   @[@@@@RA
)@@G@@.     @ @@@@DRDPKT    *         DREAD$    @^@@@@          'TPF$        'RB
)@@G@@@A@@@@          *         003401,MIBUF    @^@@@@          *         0   RC
)@@G@@@E@@@@MIBUF     RES       28                  MAIN ITEM BUFFER    @^@@@@RD
)@@G@@CSFST     RES       1   $]@@@@-272  @@@@@@@F@@@@INSIZE    +         0   RE
)@@G@@                SET FOR MAX GRANNY SPEC   @^@@@@          END       PCF RF
)@@G@@_@@@@@        FUDON               REDO DYNAMIC USE AND CONTINUE   @[@@@@RG
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@NFNDM     PRINT$    NFM,NFL             PRINT THE NOT FOUND RH
)@@G@@MESSAGE     @D@@@@      *[S@@@*SDFF*@@@@@@@ @@@@TITLE         TPF PROCESRI
)@@G@@SOR   @C@@@@OPTION T,ON    . SUPPRESS TABLE OF CONTENTS     @E@@@@ THIS RJ
)@@G@@PROCESSOR ENABLES THE USER TO DEFINE A 'TPF' FILE     @F@@@@ USED IN PLARK
)@@G@@CE OF THE ASSUMED FILE TPF$.  THE PROCESSOR IS CALLED @^@@@@ WITH THE STRL
)@@G@@ATEMENT:    @@@@@@@]@@@@ @TPF FILE. @@@@@@@F@@@@ WHERE 'FILE' MAY BE THERM
)@@G@@ FULL SPECIFICATION ALLOWED FOR FILES.    @F@@@@ IF THE SPECIFICATION CORN
)@@G@@NSISTS OF ONLY A FILE NAME, THE PERIOD    @F@@@@ MAY BE OMITTED.  IF THERO
)@@G@@ FILE IS CURRENTLY ASSIGNED TO THE RUN,   @G@@@@ THE USE NAME 'TPF$' WILRP
)@@G@@L BE ATTACHED TO THE FILE AND THE PROCESSOR     @G@@@@ WILL COMPLETE.  IRQ
)@@G@@F THE FILE IS NOT ASSIGNED, IT WILL BE DYNAMICALLY    @G@@@@ ASSIGNED WIRR
)@@G@@TH THE 'A' AND 'X' OPTIONS.  THE PROCESSOR WILL WAIT IF THE @F@@@@ FILE RS
)@@G@@IS NOT AVAILABLE.  IF THE FILE NAME PARAMETER IS OMITTED,   @F@@@@ A FILRT
)@@G@@E CALLED 'PROGFILE$' WILL BE USED.  IF NO FILE WITH THE     @F@@@@ SPECIRU
)@@G@@FIED NAME EXISTS, A NEW FILE WILL BE CREATED.  THIS ACTION  @F@@@@ WILL RV
)@@G@@BE OVERRIDDEN BY THE 'A' OPTION ON THE TPF STATEMENT, WHICH @F@@@@ WILL RW
)@@G@@CAUSE AN ERROR MESSAGE IF THE DESIRED FILE DOES NOT EXIST.  @F@@@@ IF TPRX
)@@G@@F IS CREATING A FILE, THE 'P' OPTION WILL MAKE THAT FILE    @]@@@@ PUBLIRY
)@@G@@C.    @@@@@@@E@@@@ THE 'T' OPTION ALLOWS ASSIGNING OR RE-ASSIGNING A TEMRZ
)@@G@@PORARY@E@@@@ TPF$ FILE. THIS CAN BE USEFUL WHEN WORKING IN A CATALOGUED SA
)@@G@@@F@@@@ FILE AND THEN, WHEN THROUGH, GOING BACK TO A TEMPORARY FILE.     SB
)@@G@@@@@@@@@E@@@@ IT IS ALSO POSSIBLE TO SPECIFY OTHER THAN DEFAULT FOR THE  SC
)@@G@@@E@@@@ MAX GRANULE SIZE. THIS CAN BE DONE FOR A TEMPORARY FILE BY @E@@@@SD
)@@G@@ SPECIFYING THE SIZE AS THE FIRST ELEMENT ON THE CALL CARD. @@@@@@@[@@@@SE
)@@G@@ IE.  @@@@@@@]@@@@ @TPF,T 5000@@@@@@@E@@@@ THIS WILL FREE THE CURRENT TPSF
)@@G@@F$ AND ASSIGN A NEW ONE WITH  @ @@@@ A MAX TRACK COUNT OF 5000.   @@@@@@SG
)@@G@@@E@@@@ FOR CATALOGUED FILES, THE MAX TRACK COUNT CAN BE SEPCIFIED @ @@@@SH
)@@G@@ AS THE SECOND ELEMENT NAME.  @@@@@@@[@@@@ IE.  @@@@@@@#@@@@ @TPF FILE,5SI
)@@G@@000   @@@@@@@D@@@@ THIS WILL ASSIGN (OR CATALOG) THE FILE, 'FILE', WITH SJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@ A MAX TRACK COUNT OF 5000.   @@@@@@___, 'FILE', WITH @ @@[@ A MAXSK
)@@G@@ TRACK COUNT OF 5000.   @[@@[@      ___@[@      ___ @TPF FILE,5000@[@@[@SL
)@@G@@.     @F@@[@.         THIS WILL ASSIGN (OR CATAL======@@^@@ @@@@@@@@@@@@SM

)@@G@@E-J^[DD1AD9MD*)^@)^@)^@)*[@@@@*SDFF*@D@@@@.   @TSWAP  PROCESSOR    -   GXN
)@@G@@UY PUJOL, NYU   JAN 75  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@. CALL:  @TSWAP<,OPTS>   FILENXO
)@@G@@AME.<,REEL> @[@@@@.     @]@@@@. OPTIONS:  @[@@@@.     @A@@@@. I - INITIAXP
)@@G@@LIZE TAPE FILE (TINTL$) @A@@@@. N - COM$ MSG SAYING 'NO RING'     @ @@@@XQ
)@@G@@. R - COM$ MSG SAYING 'RING'  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. SPEC1 MUST BE FILENAMEXR
)@@G@@ OF TAPE FILE ASSIGNED TO RUN.  SPEC2,    @F@@@@. IF PRESENT, INDICATES XS
)@@G@@REEL TO SWAP TO.  IF NOT GIVEN, NEXT REEL @B@@@@. IN FILE'S REEL LIST WIXT
)@@G@@LL BE ASSUMED.    @[@@@@.     @#@@@@              AXR$@B@@@@ST.         XU
)@@G@@                 . $H START   @D@@@@       L      A0,(56,INFOR)  . $P SEXV
)@@G@@T A0 FOR RINF$    @D@@@@       LMJ    X11,RINF$      . $W GET INFOR TABLXW
)@@G@@E     @D@@@@       J      MSG1A          . $J MSG1 NO INFOR TABLE @D@@@@XX
)@@G@@       L,U    A0,1           . $P SET A0 FOR SELT$    @C@@@@       LMJ  XY
)@@G@@  X11,SELT$      . $P GET FILENAME  @D@@@@       NOP                   .XZ
)@@G@@ $P DUMMY INSTRUCTION   @H@@@@       TZ,S2  ELT$           . $T IS THEREYA
)@@G@@ A CHARACTER COUNT ON THE FILENAME  @E@@@@       J      NOSUB          .YB
)@@G@@ $J NOSUB YES,THEN USE IT     @H@@@@       TNZ,S1 ELT$+1         . $T WAYC
)@@G@@S AN ELTNAME GIVEN IN FIRST SPEC FIELD    @G@@@@       J      MSG1      YD
)@@G@@     . $J MSG1 NO,THEN NO FILE WAS SPECIFIED    @C@@@@       DL     A0,EYE
)@@G@@LT$+9      . $P GET LETNAME   @E@@@@       DS     A0,ELT$+4      . $P STYF
)@@G@@ORE IN PLACE OF FILENAME@C@@@@       LA,S1  A0,ELT$+1      . $P GET CHARYG
)@@G@@ COUNT@F@@@@       S,S2   A0,ELT$        . $P STORE IN FILENAME CHAR COUYH
)@@G@@NT    @D@@@@       LA,S3  A0,ELT$+1      . $P GET ELT CYCLE COUNT @F@@@@YI
)@@G@@       SA,S3  A0,ELT$        . $P STORE AS F-CYCLE CHAR COUNT     @E@@@@YJ
)@@G@@       JZ     A0,NOSUB       . $T JUMP IF THERE WAS NONE    @C@@@@      YK
)@@G@@ LA     A0,ELT$+13     . $P GET ELTCYCLE  @D@@@@       SA     A0,ELT$+6 YL
)@@G@@     . $P STORE AS FCYCLE     @B@@@@NOSUB.                        . $H NYM
)@@G@@OSUB  @E@@@@       DL     A0,ELT$+4      . $P LOAD A0 WITH FILENAME     YN
)@@G@@@E@@@@         DS     A0,FAC         . $P STORE IN FITEM PCKT     @E@@@@YO
)@@G@@       L    A0,(12,FAC)         . $P LOAD A0 WITH FITEM PCKT@F@@@@      YP
)@@G@@ ER     FITEM$         . $P GET FITEM POOL OF THIS FILE     @G@@@@      YQ
)@@G@@ TNZ,S1  FAC+6          . $T IS THERE ANY EQUIP TYPE SPECIFIED    @H@@@@YR
)@@G@@       J      MSG2           . $J MSG2,FILE DOESNT EXIST OR HAS NO FACILYS
)@@G@@ITIES @C@@@@       L,S1   A0,FAC+6       . $P GET EQUIP TYPE@G@@@@      YT
)@@G@@ TG,U  A0,020          . $T TEST WETHER IT HAS A TAPE EQUIP TYPE  @C@@@@YU
)@@G@@       J      MSG3           . $J MSG3,NOT TAPE @D@@@@       DL     A0,TYV
)@@G@@SW         . $P FILENAME FOR USE    @A@@@@       LMJ    X11,DUSE$      .YW
)@@G@@ $P   @C@@@@OPTION L      A0,INFOR       . $P GET OPTIONS   @D@@@@      YX
)@@G@@ TEP    A0,(1*/('Z'-'N')) . $T IS NOPTION SET   @B@@@@       S      A0,NYY
)@@G@@OPT        . $P SET FLAG@C@@@@       TEP    A0,(1*/('Z'-'R')) . $T IS ROYZ
)@@G@@PT SET@D@@@@       S      A0,ROPT        . $P YES,THEN SET FLAG   @C@@@@ZA
)@@G@@       TEP    A0,(1*/('Z'-'I')) . $T IS IOPT SET@E@@@@       J      IOPTZB
)@@G@@ION        . $W IOPTION ,DO ER TINTL$     @D@@@@       L,U    A0,2      ZC
)@@G@@          . $P SET A0 FOR SELT@E@@@@       LMJ    X11,SELT$      . $W GEZD
)@@G@@T SECOND SPEC FIELD     @E@@@@       J      SWAP+2           . $J JUST DZE
)@@G@@O A STANDARD SWAP @G@@@@       TZ,S2  ELT$           . $T IS THERE A FILZF
)@@G@@ENAME TO IN ELT SPEC    @F@@@@       J      MSG4           . $J MSG4, ERZG
)@@G@@ROR ON SECOND SPEC FIELD@D@@@@       L      A0,ELT$+9      . $P GET REELZH
)@@G@@ NUMBER     @D@@@@       S      A0,REEL        . $P STORE IN SWAP PCKT  ZI
)@@G@@@D@@@@       S      A0,REELM       . $P STORE IN PRINT MSG  @C@@@@      ZJ
)@@G@@ S      A0,NO1         . $P STORE IN COM$1@D@@@@       S      A0,RO1    ZK
)@@G@@        . $P STORE IN COM$2   @C@@@@       J      SWAP           . $J SWZL
)@@G@@AP REELS    @B@@@@IOPTION.                      . $H IOPTION@E@@@@      ZM
)@@G@@ L,U    A0,TSW         . $P PLACE PKT IN H2 OF A0     @C@@@@       ER   ZN
)@@G@@  TINTL$         . $P REINITIALIZE  @D@@@@       L      A0,(12,FAC)     ZO
)@@G@@   . $P LOAD FITEM PCKT @F@@@@      ER       FITEM$             . $P GETZP
)@@G@@ FACILITIES FO FILE     @G@@@@      L        A0,FAC+11          .$P GET ZQ
)@@G@@REEL NUMBER RETURNED IN PCKT  @D@@@@       S      A0,REELM       . $P STZR
)@@G@@ORE FOR PRINT MSG @D@@@@       S      A0,NO1         . $P STORE FOR COM$ZS
)@@G@@1     @D@@@@       S      A0,RO1         . $P STORE FOR COM$2     @C@@@@ZT
)@@G@@       J      TEST                 .$J TEST     @F@@@@SWAP   LXI,U  A0,2ZU
)@@G@@           . $P SWAP FROM THIRD WORD OF PCKT    @C@@@@       J      $+2 ZV
)@@G@@           . $J $+2 SKIP THIS @C@@@@       LXI,U  A0,1           . $P STZW
)@@G@@ANDARD SWAP @G@@@@       LXM,U  A0,TSW         . $P LOAD AO WITH ADDRESSZX
)@@G@@ OF SWAP PCKT     @C@@@@       ER     TSWAP$          . $P SWAP TAPES   ZY
)@@G@@@D@@@@       L      A0,REEL        . $P GET REEL NUMBER     @C@@@@      ZZ
)@@G@@ S      A0,REELM       . $P STORE FOR MSG @E@@@@       S      A0,NO1    AA
)@@G@@     . $P STORE FOR CONSOLE MSGS    @E@@@@       S      A0,RO1         .AB
)@@G@@ $P STORE FOR CONSOLE MSGS    @B@@@@TEST.                        . $H TEAC
)@@G@@ST    @E@@@@     TNZ     NOPT             . $T IS NORING OPTION SET     AD
)@@G@@@E@@@@       J      RING           . $J IF NOT NORING MAYBE RING  @D@@@@AE
)@@G@@       L,U    A0,COM1        . $P SET UP FOR COM$     @D@@@@       ER   AF
)@@G@@  COM$           . $P SEND CONSOLE MSG    @B@@@@       J      PRINT     AG
)@@G@@     . $J PRINT   @D@@@@RING   TNZ     ROPT           . $T IS RING OPTIOAH
)@@G@@N SET @B@@@@       J      PRINT          . $J PRINT   @D@@@@       L,U  AI
)@@G@@  A0,COM2       .$P THEN LOAD RING MSG    @C@@@@       ER     COM$      AJ
)@@G@@    .$P SEND TO CONSOLE @D@@@@PRINT  L      A0,(0103,MSG)  . $P LOAD MSGAK
)@@G@@ FOR USER   @B@@@@       ER     PRINT$         . $P PRINT IT@ @@@@      AL
)@@G@@ ER     EXIT$       . $E@F@@@@MSG1   L      A0,(0100+MSGAC,MSGA) .$P MSGAM
)@@G@@ FILE NOT SPECIFIED     @B@@@@MSG1A  ER     PRINT$     . $P PRINT IT    AN
)@@G@@@ @@@@       ER     EXIT$   . $E    @E@@@@MSG2   L      A0,(0100+MSGBC,MAO
)@@G@@SGB) .$P MSG FILE NOT ASG'D   @B@@@@       ER     PRINT$      . $P PRINTAP
